<P><FONT SIZE=+1><STRONG>Meeting of the NLII in New Orleans: January 21-23, 1996</STRONG></FONT>



<P>Here is the schedule of PDL project meetings that will be held in conjunction with the National Learning Infrastructure Initiative (NLII) meeting in New Orleans.  All PDL activities are Sunday, January 21, 1996.

<UL>
<P><LI>12:30 - 2:30 pm<BR>	
PDL project meeting: Math Tools for Teachers -- Gary Wittlich, Indiana

<P><LI>1:30 - 4:30 pm<BR>	
PDL project meeting: Web Course in a Box -- Steve Saltzberg, VCU

<P><LI>3:00 - 5:00 pm	
<BR>Discussion of programming avenues for interactive math applets (this will be a technical discussion in preparation for future PDL projects) -- Steve Griffin, IAT/UNC-CH
</UL>

<P>So that we can reserve appropriate space, please email, by December 31, Barbara Bickell (<A HREF="mailto:barbara_bickell@unc.edu">barbara_bickell@ unc.edu</A>) with the numbers of people from your institution or organization who plan to attend each meeting. 

<P><FONT SIZE=+1><STRONG>NLII Preliminary Agenda and Info</STRONG></FONT>

<P>For further information on the general NLII meeting, visit <A HREF="http://educom.edu/program/nlii/meetings/orleans96/1.96.agenda.html">Educom's preliminary agenda page</A>, or contact
Pat Bartscherer of Educom [phone/fax: 518-885-1044; email: <A HREF="mailto:patb@educom.edu">patb@educom.edu</A>] 

<P><FONT SIZE=+1><STRONG>Additional Dates to Remember</STRONG></FONT>
<P><B>February 19-20, 1996:  Business meeting of the Partnership at the IAT</B> - Details and agenda will be sent after the project meetings in January, 
but we wanted you to hold the dates.

<P>After <B>January 1, 1996</B>, the PARTNERS list will be open only to members of the Partnership.  Public information about PDL activities will available 
through the list IATNEWS.  

<P>Enjoy the holiday season.  I'll see you in New Orleans.

<P><I>- <A HREF="mailto:lowell_roberts@unc.edu">Lowell Roberts</A></I>
