<P>
<A NAME="papers"></A><STRONG>Papers and Articles</STRONG>
<P>
Bailey, Sandra S. "Creating a Virtual Reality as a Perceptual Equivalence for Training." <EM>Educational Media International</EM> 31, no. 4 (December 1994): 221-23.
<P>
Chiou, Guey-Fa. "Learning Rationales and Virtual Reality Technology in Education." <EM>Journal of Educational Technology Systems</EM> 23, no. 4 (1994-95): 327-336.
<P>
D'Ignazio, Fred, Ed. "Distance Is a State of Mind: Virtual Reality on a Shoestring." <EM>Computing Teacher</EM> 22, no. 5 (February 1995): 56-58.
<P>
Fiévet, Cyril. "The 3rd Dimension of Internet." <EM>Cybersphere</EM> no. 3 (August 24, 1995). [Online.] URL <A HREF="http://www.quelm.fr/CSphere/N3/Ana3DU.html">http://www.quelm.fr/CSphere/N3/Ana3DU.html</A>
<P>
<IMG SRC="../media/gifs/new.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="NEW"> Fox, Barrett. "VRML 2.0: The Hype, Horror, and Reality of It All." <EM>3D Design</EM> 2, no. 6 (June 1996): 18-20, 22, 24.
<P>
<IMG SRC="../media/gifs/new.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="NEW"> Gray, Terrie. "Watering All the Horses: Future Directions for Technology in Education." [1996?] [Online.] URL <A HREF="http://www.cusd.chico.k12.ca.us/~tgray/3Dhorses.html">http://www.cusd.chico.k12.ca.us/~tgray/3Dhorses.html</A>
<P>
Hedburg, John "Virtual Reality in Education: Defining Researchable Issues." <EM>Educational Media International</EM> 31, no. 4 (December 1994): 214-20.
<P>
Helsel, Sandra. "Virtual Reality and Education." <EM>Educational Technology</EM> 32, no. 5 (May 1992): 38-42.
<P>
Konsynski, Benn, and Laura Joyce Moriarty. "What Does Virtual Reality Have To Do with Higher Education?" <EM>InfoTalk</EM> (September 1994). [Online.] URL <A HREF="http://www.cc.emory.edu/ITD/MMC/virtual.1.html">http://www.cc.emory.edu/ITD/MMC/virtual.1.html</A>
<P>
Leonard, Andrew. "VR for the People." <EM>Web Review</EM> (September 29 - October 12, 1995). [Online.] URL <A HREF="http://gnn.com/gnn/wr/sept29/features/vrml/index.html">http://gnn.com/gnn/wr/sept29/features/vrml/index.html</A>
<P>
Loeffler, Carl E. "Networked Virtual Reality: Applications for Industry, Education and Entertainment." <EM>Virtual Reality World</EM> 1, no. 2 (Summer 1993): g-i.
Also available online at URL <A HREF="http://www.nta.no/telektronikk/4.93.dir/Loeffler_C_E.html">http://www.nta.no/telektronikk/4.93.dir/Loeffler_C_E.html</A>
<P>
<IMG SRC="../media/gifs/new.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="NEW"> Mahoney, Diana Phillips. "Virtual Reality on the PC." <EM>Computer Graphics World</EM> 19, no. 5 (May 1996): 53-54, 56, 58, 60.
<P>
Mason, Joanna, Marek Czernuszenko, Dana Plepys, and Thomas A. DeFanti. "CAVEview: Mosaic-Based Virtual Reality." [Online.] <BR>URL <A HREF="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/SDG/IT94/Proceedings/VR/mason/CAVEview.paper.html">http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu
/SDG/IT94/Proceedings/VR/mason/CAVEview.paper.html</A>
<P>
<IMG SRC="../media/gifs/new.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="NEW"> Pesce, Mark. "VRML 2.0: For Living, Breathing, Moving Worlds." <EM>Web Developer</EM> 2, no. 2 (May/June 1996).
Also available online: URL http://www.webdeveloper.com/mayjun96/cover.html
<P>
<IMG SRC="../media/gifs/new.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="NEW"> Psotka, Joseph. "Immersive Training Systems: Virtual Reality and Education and Training." <EM>Instructional Science</EM> 23, nos. 5-6 (1995): 405-31.
<P>
Søby, Morten. "Possessed by Virtual Reality." [Online.]
URL <A HREF="http://www.ifi.uio.no/~sigar/vroslo/possessedno.html">http://www.ifi.uio.no/~sigar/vroslo/possessedno.html</A>
<P>
<IMG SRC="../media/gifs/new.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="NEW"> Vacca, John R. "3D Worlds on the Web." <EM>Computer Graphics World</EM> 19, no. 5 (May 1996): 43-46, 48, 50.
<P>
Wilson, David L. "The Internet Takes a Journey into 3rd Dimension." <EM>The Chronicle of Higher Education</EM> 42, no. 24 (February 23, 1996): A21-22.
<P>
Wilson, Jack M. "The Prototype of the Virtual Classroom." <EM>Journal of Instruction Delivery Systems</EM> 8, no. 3 (Summer 1994): 28-33.
