<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFCE7" TEXT="#00006F">
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>Reengineering Learning Environments: Bibliography</STRONG></FONT>
<P>
Compiled by Carolyn Kotlas, MSLS<BR>
Institute for Academic Technology<BR>
Last revised:  September 9, 1994
<P>
Prepared for the IAT Satellite Broadcast<BR>
<EM>Reengineering Learning Environments</EM><BR>
Presented on September 29, 1994
<P>

</CENTER>
<P>
<STRONG><EM>Readings in Higher Education</EM></STRONG>
<P>
Curry, Barbara K. <EM>Instituting Enduring Innovations: Achieving
	Continuity of Change in Higher Education</EM>. ASHE-ERIC Higher
	Education Report (0884-0040), no. 7. Washington, DC: George
	Washington University, School of Education and Human
	Development, 1992.
<P>
Geoghegan, William H. <EM>What Ever Happened to Instructional Technology?</EM>
	Norwalk, CT: IBM Corporation, 1994.<BR>
	[Available on the Web: <A HREF="http://ike.engr.washington.edu/news/whitep/whg/wpi.htm">http://ike.engr.washington.edu/news/whitep/whg/wpi.htm
</A>]
<P>
Graves, William H. "Educational Ecosystem of Information and
	Computation: Medium and Message." <EM>EDUCOM Review</EM> 28, no. 5
	(September/October 1993): 9-12.
<P>
<EM>HEIRA (Higher Education Information Resources Alliance of ARL, CAUSE,
	and EDUCOM). HEIRAlliance Executive Strategies Report #4: What
	Presidents Need to Know ... about the Payoff on the Information
	Technology Investment</EM>. Boulder, CO: CAUSE, 1994.<BR>
	[Available by email: <A HREF="mailto:heira@cause.colorado.edu">heira@cause.colorado.edu</A>  
	Message: get heira.es4]
<P>
Heterick, Robert C., Jr., ed. <EM>Reengineering Teaching and Learning in
	Higher Education: Sheltered Groves, Camelot, Windmills, and
	Malls</EM>. Professional Paper Series, no. 10. Boulder, CO: CAUSE,
	1993.
<P>
Miller, Gary E. "Long-Term Trends in Distance Education." <EM>DEOSNEWS</EM>
	[Online] 2, no. 23 (December 1992).
	[Available by email: <A HREF="mailto:listserv@psuvm.psu.edu">listserv@psuvm.psu.edu</A>  
	Message: get DEOSNEWS 92-00041]
<P>
Oblinger, Diana G. <EM>Transforming the Academy to Improve Delivery of
	Services: Redesign for Reallocation</EM>. Norwalk, CT: IBM
	Corporation, 1994.<BR>
	[Available on the Web: <A HREF="http://ike.engr.washington.edu/news/whitep/technote/hied/oblinger.txt">
http://ike.engr.washington.edu/news/whitep/technote/hied/oblinger.txt</A>] 
	<P>
Penrod, James I., and Michael G. Dolence.<EM> Reengineering: A Process for
	Transforming Higher Education</EM>. Professional Paper Series, no.
	9. Boulder, CO: CAUSE, 1992.
<P>
Short, Douglas D. "Enhancing Instructional Effectiveness: A Strategic
	Approach."Norwalk, CT: IBM Corporation, 1994. Photocopy.
<P>
Twigg, Carol. "Can Education Be 'Productive'?" <EM>EDUCOM Review</EM> 28, no. 6
	(November/December 1993): 10-12.
<P>
Wilson, Jack M., and David N. Mosher. "The Prototype of the Virtual
	Classroom." <EM>Journal of Instruction Delivery Systems</EM> 8 (Summer
	1994): 28-33.
<P>
Wilson, Jack M., E. F. Redish, and Chad McDaniel. "Building a
Comprehensive Unified Physics Learning Environment." <EM>T.H.E. Journal IBM
Higher Education Supplement</EM> (March 1992): 5-7.
<P>
<P>
<STRONG><EM>Other Relevant Readings</EM></STRONG>
<P>
Committee to Study the Impact of Information Technology on the
	Performance of Service Activities; Computer Science and
	Telecommunications Board; Commission on Physical Sciences,
	Mathematics, and Applications, National Research Council.
	<EM>Information Technology in the Service Society: A Twenty-first
	Century Lever</EM>. Washington, DC: National Academy Press, 1994.
<P>
Ettlie, J. E., W. P. Bridges, and R. D. O'Keefe. "Organization Strategy
	and Structural Differences for Radical versus Incremental
	Innovations." <EM>Management Science</EM> 30, no. 6 (1984): 682-695.
<P>
Hammer, M. "Reengineeering Work: Don't Automate, Obliterate." <EM>Harvard
	Business Review</EM> 68, no. 4 (July 1990): 104-112.
<P>
Rogers, Everett M. <EM>Diffusion of Innovations</EM>. 3d ed. New York: Free
	Press, 1983.
<P>
Saga, Vikki. "The Nature and Determinants of Information Technology
	Infusion." Ph.D diss. proposal, Department of Information and
	Management Sciences, Florida State University, 1993.
<P>
Yin, Robert K. "Life Histories of Innovations: How New Practices Become
	Routinized." <EM>Public Administration Review</EM> 4, no. 1
	(January/February 1981): 21-28.
<P>
Zaltman, Gerald, Robert Duncan, and Jonny Holbek.<EM> Innovations and
	Organizations</EM>. New York: John Wiley & Sons, 1973.
<P>
Zmud, Robert W., and L. Eugene Apple. "Measuring Technology
	Incorporation/Infusion." <EM>Journal of Product Innovation
	Management</EM> 9, no. 2 (June 1992): 148-155.
<P>
