<AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="13,1,56,22" HREF="http://www.iat.unc.edu/index.html">
<AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="58,2,99,22" HREF="http://www.iat.unc.edu/general/new.html">
<AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="102,0,160,23" HREF="http://www.iat.unc.edu/search/search.html">
<AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="162,0,239,22" HREF="http://www.iat.unc.edu/feedback/feedback.html">
<AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="241,1,293,23" HREF="http://www.iat.unc.edu/general/about.html">
<AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="294,1,374,23" HREF="http://www.iat.unc.edu/cybrary/cybrary.html">
</MAP>

</TD></TR>
</TABLE>


<PRE>	

</PRE>
<CENTER><STRONG><FONT  SIZE=+2><FONT SIZE=+3>O</FONT>nline <FONT SIZE=+3>M</FONT>usic <FONT SIZE="+3">D</FONT>emos</FONT> </STRONG> </CENTER>


<BR>
<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH="100%" CELLSPACE=1 CELLPADDING=1>
<TR>
<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP WIDTH="360">

<H3>The Demo Applications</H3>
<FONT SIZE="-1">(<STRONG>Follow the instructions to the right to download the tools necessary to run these demos.  Please note that they are not optimized for Asymetrix Neuron.</STRONG>)</FONT> <STRONG>&#187;&#187;&#187;&#187;</STRONG>	<P>



These demonstrations are interactive multimedia applications that explore how technology can inform and explicate music in new ways.  The development of these applications arises out of our interest in accommodating different learning styles and studying music interactively  and dynamically.<P>

<LI><A HREF="4seasons.tbk">Vivaldi: <I>Four Seasons</I></A><br>
Recording: <I>Sony Essential Classics SBK 47662</I>.
<P>

<LI><A HREF="Machaut.tbk">Machaut: <I>Hareu! Hareu! le feu/Helas!/Obediens</I></A><br>
Recording: <I>The Norton Recordings To Accompany The Enjoyment of Music (Shorter Version) Seventh Edition</I>, CD 1, Track 4.
<P>

<LI><A HREF="Eccstqt2.tbk">Elliott Carter: <I>String Quartet No. 2</I><BR></A>Recording:<I>Elliott Carter: String Quartets Nos. 1 & 2, The Composers Quartet on Nonesuch 9 71249-2</I>, Tracks 4-12.<P>

<LI><A HREF="Josquin.tbk">Josquin des Pres: <I>Missa L'homme arme sexti toni</A>
</I><BR>Recording: <I>Josquin: L'homme arme Masses.  The Tallis Scholars on Gimell CDGIM 019</I>, Tracks 7-11.<P>

<LI><A HREF="Stravwin.tbk">Stravinsky: <I>Symphonies of Wind Instruments</I></A><BR>A choice of two recordings: <BR>
<I>Stravinsky Symphonies: Ashkenazy and the Berlin on London 436416-2</I></A>, Track 8.<BR>
<i>Stravinsky: The Firebird: Welser-Most and the London Philharmonic on EMI Classics CDC 5 55030 2</i>, Track 25.<P>

<LI>Forthcoming: Berg: <I>Lyric Suite</I> Recordings: <BR>
<I>The Juilliard String Quartet on Sony Classical SK 66 840</I>, Tracks 9-14.<BR>
<I>The Arditti String Quartet on Auvidis Montaigne MO 789001</I>, Tracks 3-8.<P>

<LI>Forthcoming: Debussy: <I>L'Apres-midi d'un faune</I><BR>
Recording: <I>Debussy: Leonard Bernstein and the New York Philharmonic on Sony Classical  SMK 47546</I>, Track 4.<P>



<HR SIZE=6>
<P>
<I>These applications may be freely used for educational purposes as long as the author and the URL of the web page are cited.  Comments are welcome.</I><P>


<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT  WIDTH="440">
<IMG SRC="../../media/gifs/1X17pix.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="17" HEIGHT="835">


These demonstration applications require the use of the runtime CAP-Media tool and require a Windows environment (PC or PowerMAC with PC card).  <p>
<OL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cap-media.com/demos/capplay.exe">Download the CAP-Media tool</A>.
<LI>Put the downloaded <CODE>CAPPLAY.EXE</CODE> in a temporary directory.
<LI>Go to this temporary directory and run (double click on) <CODE>CAPPLAY.EXE</CODE>.
<LI>This will install the CAP-Media runtime tool and will place it in <CODE>C:\CAPMEDIA</CODE>. <BR><FONT SIZE="-1">(You cannot do any authoring with this version.)</FONT>
</OL>
<P>
To download one of the music demos to the left, 
<OL>
<LI><STRONG>Right click</STRONG> on the demo link (the underlined title).
<LI>Click on '<CODE>Save Link As</CODE>'.
<LI>Save the <CODE>.TBK</CODE> file in <CODE>C:\CAPMEDIA</CODE>.
<LI>Insert the appropriate CD in your CD-ROM drive, and click on the <CODE>.TBK</CODE> file you wish to view.
</OL>
<P>Please note that you will need the specific recording noted in the application. Timing points are keyed to that recording and most probably will not work for another recording due to differences in tempi in different performances.
<P>If you are running Windows 95, insertion of a CD in the CD-ROM drive will automatically start the CD.  Because this is accomplished in a 'non-shared' fashion, you cannot pause the sound through Cap-Media. 
<P>To prevent this problem, please do the following before you launch an application.<P>
<OL>
<LI>Choose Start.
<LI>Click on Control Panel.
<LI>Click on System.
<LI>Click on Device Manager.
<LI>Click on CD-ROM.  (This will show your CD-ROM driver as a sub-directory.)
<LI>Click on your CD-ROM driver.
<LI>Click on Settings.
<LI>Unclick Auto Insert Notification.
<LI>Click OK.
 </OL>
<P>

</DL><P>

</TABLE>
</TABLE>
