<BR><BR>
<CENTER><STRONG><FONT  SIZE=+2><FONT SIZE=+3>N</FONT>ew <FONT SIZE=+3>V</FONT>ersions of <FONT SIZE=+3>W</FONT>eb<FONT SIZE=+3>A</FONT>pp </FONT> </STRONG> </CENTER>
<BR>
<I><B>May 31, 1996</B></I>
<P><HR><P>
The <A HREF="index.html#top">WebApp</A> program has been upgraded as follows:
<UL>
<LI>16 and 32 bit 30-day trial versions for Windows are now available <a href="index.html">online</a>.
<LI>The 32 bit version has been released and is available from the <A HREF="index.html#register">distributor</a>.
<LI>Beta version .2 for the Mac is available <a href="index.html">online</a>.
</UL>
<P>
<B>Current Shipping Versions</B><P>
Version 1.1c for Windows 3.x (also works in Windows 95)<br>
Version 1.2  for Windows 95 and Windows NT<P>
<P>
<B>Enhancements</B>
<P>
<UL>
<LI>New installation programs
<LI>Auto configuration as a helper application for Netscape 2.0
<LI>30-day trial demo versions
</UL>

<B>Differences between version 1.1b and 1.1c</B>
<UL>
<LI>When running WebApp under Windows 95, it would sometimes fail to 
make the file extension associations specified in the registration 
section.
</UL>
<P>
<B>Differences between version 1.1 and 1.1b</B>
<UL>
<LI>New support for setting up the Netscape browser for use with WebApp.
<P>
<LI>The user-interface was enhanced by improving the way certain 
error conditions are handled in order to give the user more feedback. 
In particular, if WebApp can't find the command line to run the program, 
it will now tell the user instead of just exiting without warning.
<P>
<LI>Minor modifications had to be made in order to get WebApp to run 
under Windows 95 as a 16-bit Windows application.
</UL>

<BR>
