<CENTER><H2>WebApp (16-bit) Downloading and Installation Instructions</H2></CENTER>
<P><HR><P>
The following instructions tell you how to install the 16-bit
30-day trial version of WebApp. This version runs on Windows 3.1
and Windows 95. It is fully functional.
<OL>
<LI><A HREF = "wa_note.html">Download</A> (1MB) a copy of WebApp. The
downloaded file is named "wa16demo.zip". When your browser
asks you where to save the file, put it in a new empty temporary
directory (e.g. C:\TEMPDIR\).
<LI>Unzip the file (wa16demo.zip) into the same directory using WinZip or PKUNZIP.EXE.
<LI>Run the program "wa16demo.exe". This will place
all of the files needed to run the custom setup program for WebApp
on your machine in the temporary directory.
<LI>Before running the extracted "setup.exe", you should
save a bookmark to this page and then close your web browser because
the setup program will modify the configuration settings of the browser.
If you close the browser after WebApp makes these changes, then
the changes may be overwritten when the browser closes.
<LI>Run the "setup.exe" program. This program is the
WebApp custom setup program and will install WebApp on your machine
in a new directory (default C:\WEBAPPS\). After it installs webapp, 
then you will see a message indicating if it was successful in 
configuring your browser. [Note: WebApp's custom setup program will not change your autoexec.bat, config.sys or .ini files.]
<LI>You may now delete the temporary directory you created in
step 1.
<LI>If your browser was configured successfully by the setup program,
then you are ready to try out WebApp. If WebApp could not configure
your browser, then you must configure it yourself. Do this by
adding "webapp16.exe" as a helper application (also called
external viewer) for the MIME type "application/webapp."
This can be as easy as downloading this sample <A HREF="waxman.wai">chess program</A>
and supplying the location of "webapp16.exe" when prompted
by your browser. See WebApp's on-line help for more information
on how to get your web browser configured.
<LI>Now that you have WebApp installed and your Web browser properly
configured, you are ready to visit the <A HREF = "wa_arch.html">software archives</A>
to begin experiencing the dramatic difference that WebApp can
make in browsing software on the Web.
</OL>

<P>
If you have questions or comments regarding these instructions
for installing and configuring WebApp, we would appreciate hearing
from you. Send email to <A HREF = "mailto:webapp@unc.edu">webapp@unc.edu</A> or call 919-405-1927.

<BR>
