<CENTER><STRONG><FONT  SIZE=+2><FONT SIZE=+3>W</FONT>eb<FONT SIZE=+3>A</FONT>pp <FONT SIZE=+3>C</FONT>ase <FONT SIZE=+3>S</FONT>tudy </FONT> </STRONG> </CENTER>
<BR>

<H3>BlueJay Lispware</H3>
BlueJay Lispware, developer of <A HREF="http://isaac.engr.washington.edu/mathwright/">Mathwright</A>, a tool that uses the Mathkit mathematics engine for creating interactive math and science applications, had a problem.  They were attempting to use the WWW to distribute their runtime program and example content applications from an archive of interactive applications.  Even with a custom setup program for their runtime program, they found that many of the visitors to their WWW site could not complete the installation process successfully.
<P>After evaluating WebApp, BlueJay Lispware decided to scrap their custom setup program and convert their interactive math and science archives into WebApp compatible form.  Now, visitors to their site using any MS Windows-based WWW browser and WebApp simply click on the Mathwright Player reference in the WWW page and the player is downloaded, installed and launched automatically without any further interaction by the user.  After the player is installed with WebApp, individual interactive math and science books are downloaded, installed, and executed with a single mouse click.
<P>"WebApp makes it possible to automate the process of downloading the reader as well as books chosen by the user.  The decompressing of the reader and book directories, the creation of the Windows group and its corresponding icons, and the launchings of the reader with the corresponding book are all handled by WebApp.  Since one of our goals is to make these resources available to relatively unsophisticated users, the automation of the process provided by WebApp will be especially important.  
<P>"WebApp is simple to  use and will be an important tool for providing software resources via the internet."
<P><I>James White, BlueJay Lispware<BR>
W.O. Crain, Jr., Seattle Central Community College</I>

<BR>
