<BR><BR>
<CENTER><STRONG><FONT  SIZE=+2><FONT SIZE=+3>P</FONT>reparing <FONT SIZE=+3>A</FONT>pplications for <FONT SIZE=+3>I</FONT>nstallation via <FONT SIZE=+3>W</FONT>eb<FONT SIZE=+3>A</FONT>pp </FONT> </STRONG> </CENTER>
<BR>

<P>To enable users to install an application via WebApp, it is necessary
to package the application according to the WebApp protocol:
<OL>
<LI>Create a WebApp configuration file.
<LI>Create a self-extracting archive file of your application
plus the WebApp configuration file. (NOTE: Be sure to check the license for your archive software for any possible distribution restrictions.)
<LI>Change the <CODE>.exe</CODE> extension of the archive file
to <CODE>.wai</CODE> 
<LI>Put the <CODE>.wai</CODE> file on your Web server, then create a link to the associated file on your Web page.
</OL>
<P>The protocol is the same for 16- and 32-bit versions of WebApp
whether your application is 16- or 32-bit. Extensive information
on how to create and test WebApp archives is provided in the on-line
help that comes with WebApp. If you are interested in creating
a WebApp archive for your application, you may wish to download
some <A HREF="mkwebapp.wai">tools and examples</A> that will assist
you in this process.
<P>If you create some files in WebApp format for distribution on
the Internet, please let us know so that we can add your WWW site
to our list of WebApp <A HREF="wa_arch.html">software archives</A>.

<H4>WebApp Help</H4>
<P>Please tell us what information you would like to see on this
page. To reply, send email to us at <A HREF="mailto:webapp@unc.edu">webapp@unc.edu</A>.

