The following sites distribute their software in WebApp format:
<P><B>WebApp Test </B>
<P>A small <A HREF = "waxman.wai">chess program</A> is provided here to allow you to quickly test your WebApp configuration.
<P><B>BlueJay Lispware</B>
<P><A HREF="wa_case.html">BlueJay Lispware</A> distributes Mathwright -- a tool for creating interactive math and science software.  Visit the <A HREF="http://isaac.engr.washington.edu/mathwright/">Mathwright Library</A> to get a copy of the runtime version of Mathwright and "check out" some educational software.
<P><B>Institute for Academic Technology</B>
<P>The IAT is a national center helping educators better understand and use technology to benefit learning.  The IAT has developed tools to simplify the process of creating interactive multimedia and mathematics-based content.  For example, <A HREF="../express/index.html">Express Author</A> is a point-and-click tool for creating interactive multimedia without programming.

