<TITLE>Creating a Campus Network Infrastructure:  Bibliography</TITLE>
<!-- Converted to HTML format: August 1995 -->
<!-- Last revised: October 18, 1996 by Carolyn Kotlas -->
<!-- Filename = irg-15.html -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFCE7" TEXT="#00006F">
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>Creating a Campus Network Infrastructure:  Bibliography</FONT></STRONG><BR>
<P>
Compiled by: Carolyn Kotlas, MSLS<BR>
Institute for Academic Technology<BR>
Last revised: October 18, 1996
<P>
Prepared for the IAT Satellite Broadcast<BR>
<EM>Creating a Campus Network Infrastructure</EM><BR>
Presented on March 24, 1994<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>

<STRONG>Books and Articles</STRONG>
<P>
Ahmadi, Hamid. "Wireless LANs -- A Tutorial." Paper presented at the
	18th conference of the IEEE, Minneapolis, September 1993.
<P>
Calhoun, George. <EM>Wireless Access and the Local Telephone Network</EM>.
	Boston: Artech House, 1992.
<P>
Griffin, Steve. <EM>Creating a Campus Network Infrastructure</EM>. Research
	Triangle Park, NC: Institute for Academic Technology, 1994.
	Available electronically:<BR>
	<A HREF="http://www.iat.unc.edu/publications/technotes/teknote4.txt">http://www.iat.unc.edu/publications/technotes/teknote4.txt</A>
<P>
<EM>High-Speed Networking Technology: An Introductory Survey</EM> (GG24-3816-01,
	June 1993). Raleigh, NC: International Business Machines Corp.
	International Technical Support Center, 1993.
<P>
Hinners, Bonny, ed. <EM>LAN Glossary; Supplement to LAN Magazine</EM>. San
	Francisco: Miller Freeman Publications, Inc., 1990.
<P>
<EM>IEEE Network</EM> 5 (November 1991), entire issue.
<P>
Perry, Doane. "Will Wireless LANs Realize Their Potential?" <EM>Business
	Communications Review</EM>, 23 (August 1993).
<P>
Scholtz, R. A. "The Origins of Spread Spectrum Communications." <EM>IEEE
	Transactions on Communications</EM> 30 (May 1982).
<P>
Spewak, Steven H. <EM>Enterprise Architecture Planning: Developing a
	Blueprint for Data, Applications and Technology</EM>. Boston: QED
	Publishing Group, 1993.
<P>
Spohn, Darren L. <EM>Data Network Design</EM>. New York: McGraw-Hill, 1993.
<P>

<STRONG>Magazines and Journals</STRONG>
<P>
<EM>CIO: The Magazine for Information Executives</EM>. [ISSN 0894-9301]	Framingham, MA: CIO Publishing, Inc.  
 <A HREF="http://www.cio.com">http://www.cio.com</A>
<P>
<EM>IEEE Network: The Magazine of Computer Communications</EM>. [ISSN:
	0890-8044] New York: Institute of Electrical and Electronics
	Engineers.
<P>
<EM>IEEE Transactions on Communications</EM>. [ISSN: 0090-6778] New York:
	Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers.
<P>
<EM>LAN: The Network Solutions Magazine</EM>. [ISSN: 1069-5621] San Francisco,
	CA: Miller Freeman.  <A HREF="http://www.lanmag.com/cover/ncover.html">
http://www.lanmag.com/cover/ncover.html</A>
<P>
<EM>LAN Times</EM>. [ISSN: 1040-5917] New York: McGraw-Hill, Inc.  <A HREF="http://www.wcmh.com/lantimes/index.html">
http://www.wcmh.com/lantimes/index.html</A>
<P>
<EM>Network Computing</EM>. [ISSN: 1046-4468] Manhasset, NY: CMP Publications.  
 <A HREF="http://techweb.cmp.com:80/techweb/nc/current/">
http://techweb.cmp.com:80/techweb/nc/current/</A>
<P>
<EM>Network World; the Newsweekly of Enterprise Network Computing</EM>. [ISSN:
	0887-7661] Framingham, MA: Network World, Inc.  
<A HREF="http://www.nwfusion.com/">
http://www.nwfusion.com/</A>
<P>
<EM>Networking Management</EM>. [ISSN: 1052-049X] Tulsa, OK: PennWell Publishing
	Co.
<P>

<STRONG>Standards and Bulletins</STRONG>
<P>
(Approved Standards and Bulletins are available for a fee from Global
Engineering Documents, 800-854-7179.)
<P>
<EM>TSB-36: Additional Cable Specifications for Unshielded Twisted Pair
	Cables</EM>, November 1991.
<P>
<EM>TSB-40: Additional Transmission Specifications for Unshielded Twisted
	Pair Connecting Hardware</EM>, August 1992.
