<HEAD>
<TITLE>User Interface Design:  Bibliography</TITLE>
<!-- Converted to HTML format: August 1995 -->
<!-- Last revised: October 11, 1996 by Carolyn Kotlas -->
<!-- Filename = irg-05.html -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFCE7" TEXT="#00006F">
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>User Interface Design: Bibliography</STRONG></FONT>
<P>
Compiled by: Carolyn Kotlas, MSLS<BR>
Institute for Academic Technology<BR>
Last revised: October 11, 1996
</CENTER>
<P>
Aspillaga, Macarena. "Implications of Screen Design upon Learning."
	<EM>Journal of Educational Technology Systems</EM> 20, no. 1 (1991-92):
	53-58.
<P>
Aspillaga, Macarena. "Screen Design: Location of Information and Its
	Effects on Learning." <EM>Journal of Computer-Based Instruction</EM> 18,
	no. 3 (1991): 89-92.
<P>
Banks, William W., and Jon Weimer. <EM>Effective Computer Display Design</EM>.
	Englewood Cliffs, NJ: Prentice Hall, 1992.
<P>
Barfield, Lon. <EM>The User Interface: Concepts & Design</EM>. Reading, MA:
	Addison-Wesley Pub. Co., 1993.
<P>
Benbasat, Izak, and P. Todd. "An Experimental Investigation of
	Interface Design Alternatives: Icon vs. Text and Direct
	Manipulation vs. Menus."<EM> International Journal of Man-Machine
	Studies</EM> 38, no. 3 (1993): 369-402.
<P>
Bielenberg, Daniel R. "Interactive Design and the Mythical 'Intuitive
	User Interface.'" <EM>Journal of Interactive Instruction
	Development</EM> 6, no. 2 (1993): 14-19.
<P>
Blattner, Meera M., and Roger B. Dannenberg, eds. <EM>Multimedia Interface
	Design</EM>. Reading, MA: Addison-Wesley Pub., 1992.
<P>
Chapman, William. "Color Coding and Interactivity of Multimedia."
	<EM>Journal of Educational Multimedia and Hypermedia</EM> 2, no. 1
	(1993): 3-23.
<P>
Coll, Joan H., et al. "The Blinking Cursor: a Two-Experiment Sequence
	Investigating Whether a Blinking Cursor Facilitates User
	Performance." <EM>International Journal of Man-Machine Studies</EM> 39,
	no. 2 (1993): 177-185.
<P>
Cox, Kevin, and David Walker. <EM>User-Interface Design</EM>. New York: Prentice
	Hall, 1993.
<P>
Dringus, Laurie P. "Interface Issues Associated with Using 
	the Internet as a Link to Online Courses." <EM>Journal of Interactive Instruction
	Development</EM> 8, no. 2 (Fall 1995): 16-20.
<P>
Dumas, Joseph S. D<EM>esigning User Interfaces for Software</EM>. Englewood
	Cliffs, NJ: Prentice Hall, 1988.
<P>
Eberts, Ray E. <EM>User Interface Design</EM>. Englewood Cliffs, NJ: Prentice
	Hall, 1994.
<P>
Emery, D. "Developing Effective Instructional Graphics." <EM>Journal of
	Interactive Instruction Development</EM> 6, no. 2 (1993): 20-24.
<P>
Emurian, Henry H. "Some Effects of Row, Diagonal, and Column Screen
	Formats on Search Time and Strategy." <EM>Computers in Human
	Behavior</EM> 6, no. 2 (1990): 153-66.
<P>
Faiola, Tony. "Designing a Visual Factors-Based Screen Display
	Interface: The New Role of the Graphic Technologist."
	<EM>Educational Technology</EM> 28, no. 8 (1988): 12-21.
<P>
Fowler, Susan, and Victor Stanwick. <EM>The GUI Style 
	Guide</EM>. Boston: AP Professional, 1995.
<P>
Galitz, Wilbert O. <EM>User-Interface Screen Design</EM>. Boston: QED Pub.
	Group, 1993.
<P>
Grabinger, R. Scott. "Computer Screen Designs: Viewer Judgments."
	<EM>Educational Technology Research and Development </EM>41, no. 2
	(1993): 35-73.
<P>
Grabinger, R. Scott. "CRT Text Layout: Perceptions of Viewers."
	<EM>Computers in Human Behavior</EM> 4, no. 3 (1988): 189-205.
<P>
Grabinger, R. Scott. "The Effect of CRT Screen Design on Learning." In
	<EM>Proceedings of Selected Research Papers</EM>. New Orleans, LA:
	Association for Educational Communications and Technology,
	1988.
<P>
Grabinger, R. Scott. "Screen Layout Design: Research into the Overall
	Appearance of the Screen."<EM> Computers in Human Behavior</EM> 5, no. 3
	(1989): 175-83.
<P>
Hannafin, Michael J. "An Integrated Framework for CBI Screen Design and
	Layout." <EM>Computers in Human Behavior</EM> 5, no. 3 (1989): 155-65.
<P>
Heckel, Paul. <EM>The Elements of Friendly Software Design</EM>. San Francisco:
	Sybex, Inc., 1991.
<P>
Hedberg, John G., B. Harper, and C. Brown. " Reducing Cognitive Load in
	Multimedia Navigation." <EM>Australian Journal of Educational
	Technology</EM> 9, no. 2 (1993): 157-81.
<P>
Hillman, D. C. A., D. J. Willis, and C. N. Gunawardena.
	"Learner-Interface Interaction in Distance Education: An
	Extension of Contemporary Models and Strategies for
	Practitioners." <EM>American Journal of Distance Education</EM> 8, no. 2
	(1994): 30-42.
<P>
Horton, William. <EM>Illustrating Computer Documentation: the Art of
	Presenting Information Graphically on Paper and Online</EM>. New
	York: John Wiley & Sons, 1991.
<P>
Hunka, S. "Design Guidelines for CAI Authoring Systems." <EM>Educational
	Technology</EM> 29, no. 11 (1989): 12-17.
<P>
Isaacs, G. "Text Screen Design for Computer-Assisted Learning." <EM>British
	Journal of Educational Technology</EM> 18, no.1 (1987): 41-51.
<P>
Jonassen, David H. "Functions, Applications, and Design Guidelines for
	Multiple Window Environments." <EM>Computers in Human Behavior</EM> 5,
	no. 3 (1989): 185-94.
<P>
Jones, Mark K. <EM>Human-Computer Interaction: A Design Guide</EM>. Englewood
	Cliffs, NJ: Educational Technology Publications, 1989.
<P>
Jones, Marshall G., John D. Farquhar, and Daniel W. Surry. "Using Metacognitive Theories
 	to Design User Interfaces for Computer-Based Learning." 
	<EM>Educational Technology</EM> 35, no. 4 (July/August 1995): 12-22.
<P>
Kristof, Ray, and Amy Satran. <EM>Interactivity by Design: 
	Creating & Communicating with New Media</EM>. Mountain View, CA: Adobe Press, 1995.
<P>
Laurel, Brenda, ed.<EM> The Art of Human-Computer Interface Design.
	Reading</EM>, MA: Addison-Wesley Pub. Co., 1990.
<P>
McFarland, Ronald D. "Ten Design Points for the Human Interface to
	Instructional Multimedia." <EM>T.H.E. Journal</EM> 22, no. 7 (February
	1995): 67-69.
<P>
Milheim, William D. "Screen Design for Computer-Based Training and
	Interactive Video: Practical Suggestions and Overall
	Guidelines." <EM>Performance and Instruction</EM> 31, no. 5 (1992):
	13-21.
<P>
Misanchuk, Earl R., and R. A. Schwier. "The 
	Mythology of Colour in Mutimedia Screen 
	Design: Art, Science and Connoiseurship." <EM>Canadian Journal of 
	Educational Communication</EM> 24, no. 1 (1995): 3-26.
<P>
Morrison, Gary R., et al. "Implications for the Design of Computer-Based
	Instruction Screens."<EM> Computers in Human Behavior</EM> 5, no. 3
	(1989): 167-73.
<P>
Nibley, M. "Words and Pictures: Scripting and Producing the Multimedia
	Educational Program." <EM>Journal of Interactive Instruction
	Development</EM> 6, no. 2 (1993): 10-13.
<P>
Norman, Donald A. <EM>The Design of Everyday Things</EM>. New York: Doubleday,
	1990.
<P>
Norman, Donald A., and Stephen W. Draper, eds. <EM>User Centered System
	Design: New Perspectives on Human-Computer Interaction</EM>.
	Hillsdale, NJ: L. Erlbaum Associates, 1986.
<P>
Norman, Kent L. "Navigating the Educational Space with
	Hypercourseware." <EM>Hypermedia</EM> 6, no. 1 (1994): 35-60.
<P>
Orr, K. L., K. C. Golas, and K. Yao. "Storyboard Development for
	Interactive Multimedia Training." <EM>Journal of Interactive
	Instruction Development</EM> 6, no. 3 (1993): 18-31.
<P>
Park, Ok-Choon, and R. Hopkins. "Instructional Conditions for Using
	Dynamic Visual Displays: A Review." <EM>Instructional Science</EM> 21,
	no. 6 (1993): 427-49.
<P>
<IMG  SRC="../media/gifs/new.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="New"> Pett, Dennis, and Trudy Wilson. "Color Research and Its Application to the 	Design of Instructional Materials." <EM>Educational Technology 	Research and Development</EM> 44, no. 3 (1996): 19-35.
<P>
Price, Robert V. <EM>Computer-aided Instruction: A Guide for Authors</EM>.
	Belmont, CA: Wadsworth, 1991.
<P>
Rosendahl-Kreitman, Kristee. <EM>User Interface Design Workbook</EM>. Santa
	Clara, CA Multimedia Computing Corp., 1990.
<P>
Rubin, Tony. <EM>User Interface Design for Computer 
	Systems</EM>. New York: Halsted Press, 1988.
<P>
Sassoon, R. "Closing the Gap between Computers and Typography."
	<EM>Advanced Information Systems </EM>1, no. 1 (1993): 27-29.
<P>
Sassoon, R., ed.  <EM>Computers and Typography</EM>. Oxford: Intellect, Ltd,
	1993.
<P>
Schaefermeyer, Shanna. "Standards for Instructional Computing Software
	Design and Development." <EM>Educational Technology</EM> 30, no.
	6(1990): 9-15.
<P>
Schwier, Richard A., and Earl R. Misanchuk. 
	"Designing Multimedia for the Hypertext 
	Markup Language." <EM>Journal of Interactive Instruction Development</EM> 8, 
	no. 4 (Spring 1996): 15-25. 
<P>
Schwier, Richard A., and Earl R. Misanchuk. <EM>Interactive Multimedia
	Instruction</EM>. Englewood Cliffs, NJ: Educational Technology
	Publications, 1993.
<P>
Shneiderman, Ben.<EM> Designing the User Interface: Strategies for
	Effective Human-Computer Interaction</EM>. Reading, MA:
	Addison-Wesley, 1992.
<P>
Strauss, Roy. "Some Basics of Screen Design for Television-based
	Multimedia." <EM>Multimedia & Videodisc Monitor</EM> (November 1991):
	24-28.
<P>
Taylor, C. David. "Choosing a Display Format for 
	Instructional Multimedia: Two Screens vs. One." Paper presented at the Convention 
	of the Association for Educational Communications and Technology, Washington, 
	DC, February 5-9, 1992.
<P>
Thimbleby, Harold. <EM>User Interface Design</EM>. New York: Reading, MA:
	Addison-Wesley Pub., 1990.
<P>
Thomas, P., and R. Macredie. "Games and the Design of Human-Computer
	Interfaces." <EM>Educational & Training Technology International</EM>
	31, no. 2 (1994): 134-42.
<P>
Tognazzini, Bruce.<EM> Tog on Interface</EM>. Reading, MA: Addison-Wesley, 1992.
<P>
Treu, Siegfried.<EM> User Interface Design: A Structured Approach</EM>. New
	York: Plenum Press, 1994.
<P>
Tufte, Edward R. <EM>Envisioning Information</EM>. Cheshire, CT: Graphics Press,
	1990.
<P>
Tufte, Edward. "The User Interface: The Point of Competition." <EM>Bulletin
	of the American Society for Information Science</EM> 18, no. 5
	(1992): 15-17.
<P>
Waterworth, John A.<EM> Multimedia Interaction with Computers: Human
	Factors Issues</EM>. New York: Ellis Harwood, 1992.
<P>
White, Jan V. <EM>Color for the Electronic Age</EM>. New York: Watson-Guptill
	Publications, 1990.
<P>
White, Jan V. <EM>Graphic Design for the Electronic Age</EM>. New York:
	Watson-Guptill Publications, 1988.
<P>
