<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE></TITLE>
<!-- Created:  May 8, 1996 by Carolyn Kotlas -->
<!-- Last revised: -->
<!-- Filename = irg-24.html -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFCE7" TEXT="#00006F">
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>Collections of Software by Discipline: Selected Samples
</STRONG></FONT>
<P>
Compiled by: Carolyn Kotlas<BR>
Institute for Academic Technology<BR>
Last revised: May 8, 1996
</CENTER>
<P>
A sampling of collections of educational software representing several selected disciplines. Web addresses that provide links to the collections are included with each example.
<BR><BR>
<A HREF="#biology">Biology</A><BR>
<A HREF="#chemistry">Chemistry </A><BR>
<A HREF="#engineering">Engineering</A> <BR>
<A HREF="#environment">Environmental Sciences</A> <BR>
<A HREF="#math">Mathematics </A><BR>
<A HREF="#physics">Physics </A><BR>
<A HREF="#polisci">Political Science</A><BR> 
<A HREF="#statistics">Statistics Education </A>
<BR><BR><BR>

<A NAME="biology"></A><STRONG><EM>Biology</EM></STRONG>
<P>
<STRONG>Biology Education Software Taskforce of the University of Washington</STRONG><BR>
Maintains a list of software collections covering biology education and specialized collections in the areas of ecology and evolution; physiology and neurobiology; cell, molecular biology and genetics.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.zoology.washington.edu/biosoft/">http://www.zoology.washington.edu/biosoft/</A>
<P>
<STRONG>BioQUEST Curriculum Consortium</STRONG><BR>
The BioQUEST Curriculum Consortium, a network of educators, biologists, science educators, and others, has established an electronic academic journal of peer-reviewed, nationally tested biological educational materials that is committed to publishing and recognizing the highest quality designs and implementations of research-like opportunities for students.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.biology.iupui.edu/BioQUEST/bioquestlib.html">http://www.biology.iupui.edu/BioQUEST/bioquestlib.html</A>
<BR><BR><BR>

<A NAME="chemistry"></A><STRONG><EM>Chemistry</EM></STRONG>
<P>
<STRONG>JCE: Software</STRONG><BR>
JCE: Software is the branch of the Journal of Chemical Education that publishes instructional computer software and videodiscs.
<P>
	<A HREF="http://jchemed.chem.wisc.edu/JCESoft/">http://jchemed.chem.wisc.edu/JCESoft/</A>
<BR><BR><BR>

<A NAME="engineering"></A><STRONG><EM>Engineering</EM></STRONG>
<P>
<STRONG>National Engineering Education Delivery System</STRONG><BR>
NEEDS is an online database of multimedia engineering courseware and other educational material. Originally containing courseware developed by Synthesis, a National Engineering Education Coalition, the NEEDS database is expanding to include quality courseware nationwide.
<P>
	<A HREF="http://www.needs.org/">http://www.needs.org/</A>
<BR><BR><BR>

<A NAME="environment"></A><STRONG><EM>Environmental Sciences</EM></STRONG>
<P>
<STRONG>CTI CLUES</STRONG><BR>
Resources for computer-based learning in Land Use and Environmental Sciences, including animal science and management, aquaculture, business management, crop and grassland science and management, environmental science, food science, forestry, general land use, geographical information systems, horticulture, rural economics, soil science, and statistics and econometrics.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.clues.abdn.ac.uk:8080/directory/subjects/subjects.html">http://www.clues.abdn.ac.uk:8080/directory/subjects/subjects.html</A>
<BR><BR><BR>

<A NAME="math"></A><STRONG><EM>Mathematics</EM></STRONG>
<P>
<STRONG>Math Archives</STRONG><BR>
The primary emphasis is on materials which are used in the teaching of mathematics. Currently the Archives is particularly strong in its collection of educational software. Other areas, ranging from laboratory notebooks and problem sets to lecture notes and reports on innovative methods, are growing.
<P>
<A HREF="http://archives.math.utk.edu/software.html">http://archives.math.utk.edu/software.html</A>
<BR><BR><BR>

<A NAME="physics"></A><EM><STRONG>Physics</STRONG></EM>
<P>
<STRONG>Physics Academic Software</STRONG><BR>
Physics Academic Software (PAS) is a software publishing project of the American Institute of Physics (AIP) in cooperation with The American Physical Society (APS) and the American Association of Physics Teachers (AAPT).
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.aip.org/pas/pashome.html">http://www.aip.org/pas/pashome.html</A>
<BR><BR><BR>

<A NAME="polisci"></A><STRONG><EM>Political Science</EM></STRONG>
<P>
<STRONG>Brown & Benchmark Political Science Catalog</STRONG><BR>
Feature faculty-developed political science software in the areas of American government and politics, American public policy, Canadian politics, comparative politics, Congress, environmental politics, ethnic and minority politics, foreign policy, international relations, international studies, introductory political science, judicial politics, political science research methods.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.bbp.com/catalogs/polisci.html">http://www.bbp.com/catalogs/polisci.html</A>
<BR><BR><BR>

<A NAME="statistics"></A><STRONG><EM>Statistics Education</EM></STRONG>
<P>
<STRONG>Journal of Statistics Education Information Service -- Software</STRONG><BR>
The Journal of Statistics Education maintains this information center with software collections for the convenience of its readers.
<P>
<A HREF="gopher://jse.stat.ncsu.edu/11/software/stats">gopher://jse.stat.ncsu.edu/11/software/stats</A>
<P>
<HR>
<FONT SIZE=-1>
<STRONG>URL</STRONG>: <A HREF="http://www.iat.unc.edu/guides/irg24.html">http://www.iat.unc.edu/guides/irg24.html</A><BR>
© <A HREF="../general/copyright.html">Copyright</A> 1996, Institute for Academic Technology. All rights reserved.
</FONT>
