<HEAD>
<TITLE>Using Computers to Teach Basic Skills:  Bibliography</TITLE>
<!-- Converted to HTML format: August 1995 by Carolyn Kotlas -->
<!-- Last revised: -->
<!-- Filename = irg-01.html -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFCE7" TEXT="#00006F">
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>Using Computers to Teach Basic Skills: Bibliography</STRONG></FONT>
<P>
Compiled by: Carolyn Kotlas, MSLS<BR>
Institute for Academic Technology<BR>
Last revised: February 14, 1995
</CENTER>
<P>
Adams, Dennis. "Creativity, Basic Skills and Computing: A Conceptual
	Intersection with Implications for Education." <EM>Journal of
	Creative Behavior</EM> 23, no. 4 (1989): 258-62.
<P>
Anandam, Kamala. "Project SYNERGY: Software Support of Underprepared
	Students." <EM>T.H.E. Journal, IBM Higher Education Supplement</EM>
	(March 1992): 26-28.<BR>
<P>
Askov, Eunice N. "Using Computers for Teaching Basic Skills to Adults."
	<EM>Lifelong Learning </EM>12, no. 6  (1989): 28-31.
<P>
Becker, H. J. "Computer-Based Integrated Learning Systems in the
	Elementary and Middle Grades: A Critical Review and Synthesis
	of Evaluation Reports." <EM>Journal of Educational Computing
	Research</EM> 8, no. 1 (1992): 1-41.
<P>
Becker, H. J. "A Model for Improving the Performance of Integrated
	Learning." <EM>Educational Technology</EM> 32, no. 9 (1992): 6-15.
<P>
Block, S. H. "Applying Technology to Workforce Training."<EM> Interactive
	Learning International</EM> 8, no. 4 (1992): 311-314.
<P>
Brown, H. M., and P. G. Minton. "Classroom 2000: A Room with a View of
	the Future." <EM>T.H.E. Journal</EM> 20, no. 8 (1993): 65-70.
<P>
Dasher, Joan M. "Multimedia Solutions for the Basic Skills Crisis in
	America." <EM>Journal of Instruction Delivery Systems</EM> 9, no. 1
	(Winter 1995): 3-5.
<P>
Dees, Anne. "Basic Skills Go High Tech." Vocational Education Journal
	65, no. 1 (1990): 30-32.
<P>
Glenn, Craig. "Results of Using CAI to Improve Performance in Basic
	Skills Areas." <EM>T.H.E. Journal</EM> 15, no. 10 (1988): 61-64.
<P>
Jorgenson, E. "Missouri's Basic Education Initiative Supports Job
	Training." <EM>T.H.E. Journal</EM> 19, no. 8 (1992): 60-62.
<P>
Karlstein, Patricia J. "Fighting High School Illiteracy: The PALS
	Project in Brooklyn." <EM>T.H.E. Journal, IBM PCs & Compatibles
	Special Issue</EM> (1988): 49-54.
<P>
Kenworthy, N. W. "When Johnny Can't Read: Multimedia Design Strategies
	to Accommodate Poor Readers." <EM>Journal of Instruction Delivery
	Systems</EM> 7, no. 1 (1993): 27-30.
<P>
Kiefer, K. "Should Basic Writers Use Text Analysis Software?"
	<EM>Collegiate Microcomputer</EM> 10, no. 4 (1992): 204-208.
<P>
Novoa, Irma. "Investing in the Future with Comprehensive Competencies."
	<EM>T.H.E. Journal, IBM PCs & Compatibles Special Issue</EM> (1988):
	71-77.
<P>
Quinn, Clark N., et al. "Designing Multimedia Environments for Thinking
	Skill Practice."<EM> Journal of Educational Multimedia and
	Hypermedia</EM> 2, no. 4 (1993): 405-416.
<P>
Tetenbaum, Toby Jane. "Computers as an Agent for Educational Change."
	<EM>Computers in the Schools</EM> 2, no. 4 (1985-86): 91-103.
<P>
Vacc, N. N. "A Comparison of Using a Microcomputer, Precision Teaching
	and Worksheets to Master Basic Multiplication Facts." <EM>Journal
	of Educational Technology</EM> 20, no. 3 (1992): 179-198.
<P>
Watkins, Beverly T. "Using Computers to Teach Basic Skills." <EM>Chronicle
	of Higher Education</EM> 38, no. 6 (1991): A23-A26.
<P>
Wilson, Lois S. "An On-Line Prescription for Basic Skills."<EM> Training
	and Development Journal</EM> 44, no. 4 (1990): 36-41.
<P>
