<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFCE7" TEXT="#00006F">
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>Technology and Higher Education Statistics, Surveys, and Reports</STRONG></FONT>
<P>
Compiled by: Carolyn Kotlas</A>, MSLS<BR>
Institute for Academic Technology<BR>
Last revised: June 20, 1996
</CENTER>
<P>
Printed and electronic sources of statistics and other survey information in the field of education, with particular emphasis on higher education and the impact of technology on education. Some links to government sources of population and economic statistics that may be correlated to education and technology are also included.
<P>
American Association of State Colleges and Universities. <I>On the Brink. Report on the Use and Management of Information Technology at AASCU Institutions</I>. Washington: AAASCU, 1995.
<P>
American Association of State Colleges and Universities.<I>1995 Report of the States</I>. Washington: AASCU, 1995.<BR>
An annual examination of the status of higher education at four-year state colleges, covering student charges, enrollments, retention, technology use in instruction, current policy issues for public colleges, state appropriations, state-funded student aid and accountability reporting.<BR>
More information is available at <A HREF="http://www.ags.com/market/AASCU/aascu.htm">http://www.ags.com/market/AASCU/aascu.htm</A>
<P>
<I>American Demographics</I>. Ithaca, NY: American Demographics Inc.<BR>
Articles cover demographic trends and consumer economics from a business marketing perspective.<BR>
Portions of several related publications available online at  
<A HREF="http://www.marketingtools.com/">http://www.marketingtools.com/</A> or <A HREF="http://www.demographics.com/">http://www.demographics.com/</A>
<P>
CAUSE. <I>CAUSE Institution Database Service</I>. Boulder, CO: CAUSE.<BR>
CAUSE is an international repository for data on information
technology in higher education.<BR>
More information is available at 
<A HREF="http://cause-www.colorado.edu/information-resources/id-service.html">http://cause-www.colorado.edu/information-resources/id-service.html</A>
<P>
Green, Kenneth C. <I>Campus Computing 1995: The Sixth National Survey of Desktop Computing in Higher Education</I>. Encino, CA: Campus Computing, 1996.<BR>
Begun in 1990, this annual survey is the largest continuing study of campus planning, policies and procedures related to the use of desktop computers in American higher education.<BR>
Copies available for $35 from Campus Computing, P. O. Box 261242, Encino, CA 91426-1242 USA; tel: 818-990-2212; email cgreen@earthlink.net
<P>
<I>The Higher Education Research Meta-Index</I>. <BR>
Designed specifically for Institutional Researchers and the educational research community at large.<BR>
 <A HREF="http://www.irp.panam.edu/more_html/utpa_erlist.html">http://www.irp.panam.edu/more_html/utpa_erlist.html</A>
<P>
Massa, Tod R. <I>The Electronic Factbook Clearinghouse</I>.<BR>
Links to statistical data for and about the various colleges and universities.<BR>
 <A HREF="http://www.willamette.edu:80/~tmassa/factbooks/">http://www.willamette.edu:80/~tmassa/factbooks/</A>
<P>
Quality Education Data. <I>Technology Trends in U.S. Public Schools</I>.<BR>
Graphs representing results of 1994-95 annual survey of virtually all public schools in the U.S. (more than 80%) for technology usage.<BR>
 <A HREF="http://www.edshow.com/QED/">http://www.edshow.com/QED/</A>
