<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>Internet Op/Ed</FONT></STRONG>
<P>
Compiled by: Carolyn Kotlas, MSLS<BR>
Institute for Academic Technology<BR>
Last revised: December 11, 1995
</CENTER>
<P>
Opinions, editorials, provocations, criticisms, commentaries, rantings, and ragings about the Internet and Internet-related topics. A hodgepodge of bias, attitude, scholarship, and reflection.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.suck.com/">Suck</A>: Daily postings by The Society of Sucksters
<P>
<A HREF="http://cyberwerks.com:70/1/cyberwire">CyberWire Dispatch</A>, by Brock N. Meeks
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.clark.net/pub/robert/">Seidman's Online Insider</A>: A Weekly Summary of Events in the Consumer Online Services Industry, by Robert Seidman
<P>
Hotwired's <A HREF="http://vip.hotwired.com/flux/">Flux</A>, by Ned Brainard <BR>
Requires member registration to access; membership is free.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.eff.org/pub/EFF/Newsletters/EFFector/">EFFector Online</A>: A Publication of the Electronic Frontier Foundation
<P>
<A HREF="http://users.aol.com/CompNote/home.html">CompuNotes</A>: A weekly publication covering the IBM computing world with software/hardware reviews, news, hot web sites, cool FTP
files and interviews, edited by Patrick Grote
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.clark.net/pub/jeffd/nuggets.html">Stamper's News Nuggets</A>: The Right Side of the Web, by Chris Stamper
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.hanover.edu/philos/ejournal/home.html">EJournal</A>: An electronic peer-reviewed journal concerned with the implications of electronic networks and texts
<P>
<A HREF="http://cyberwerks.com:70/1/jacking.in">Jacking In</A>: A Series on Cyberspace Literacy</A>
<P>
