<HEAD>
<TITLE>Libraries: Today's Issues, Tomorrow's Challenges: Bibliography</TITLE>
<!-- Created October 1994 by Carolyn Kotlas -->
<!-- Converted to HTML format August 1995 -->
<!-- Last revised: April 13, 1995 by Carolyn Kotlas -->
<!-- Filename = irg-17.html -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFCE7" TEXT="#00006F">
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>Libraries: Today's Issues, Tomorrow's Challenges: Bibliography</FONT></STRONG>
<P>
Compiled by: Carolyn Kotlas, MSLS<BR>
Institute for Academic Technology<BR>
Last revised: April 13, 1995
<P>
Prepared for the IAT Satellite Broadcast<BR>
<EM>Libraries: Today's Issues, Tomorrow's Challenges</EM><BR>
Presented on December 1, 1994<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
Barker, Philip. "Electronic Libraries -- Visions of the Future." <EM>The
	Electronic Library</EM> 12, no. 4 (August 1994): 221-29.
<P>
Bearman, Toni Carbo. Information Transforming Society: Challenges for
	the Year 2000. <EM>Information Services and Use</EM> 12, no. 3 (1992):
	217-23.
<P>
Berry, John N., III. "The Internet Is Not the Library -- Yet." <EM>Library
	Journa</EM>l 119, no. 9 (May 15, 1994): 6.
<P>
Berry, John N., III. "Showdown at the NII Gap: Libraries Must Still Be
	the Doorway to Human Interaction." <EM>Library Journal</EM> 119, no. 17
	(October 15, 1994): 6.
<P>
Brandreth, Michael, and Clare MacKeigan. "Electronic Document Delivery
	- Towards the Virtual Library."<EM> Interlending & Document
	Supply: The Journal of the British Library Lending Division</EM>
	22, no. 1 (1994): 15-19.
<P>
Campbell, Jerry D. "Choosing to Have a Future." <EM>American Libraries</EM> 24,
	no. 6 (June 1993): 560, 562, 564, 566.
<P>
Chiang, Win-Shin S., and Nancy E. Elkington, eds. <EM>Electronic Access to
	Information: A New Service Paradigm</EM>. Proceedings from a
	Symposium held July 23 through 24, 1993, Palo Alto,
	California. Mountain View, CA: Research Libraries Group, 1994.
<P>
Cloyes, Kay. "The Journey from Vision to Reality of a Virtual Library."
	<EM>Special Libraries</EM> 85, no. 4 (Fall 1994): 253-57.
<P>
Conable, Gordon M. "The Cloudy Crystal Ball: Some Future Library
	Predictions to rival Jeanne Dixon's." <EM>Library Journal</EM> 118, no.
	5 (March 15 1993): 44-45.
<P>
Coyle, Karen. "Access: Not Just Wires." Paper presented at the annual
	meeting of the Computer Professionals for Social
	Responsibility (CPSR), San Diego, CA, October 1994.
<P>
Davenport, Thomas H. "Saving IT's Soul: Human-Centered Information
	Management." <EM>Harvard Business Review</EM> 72, no. 2 (March/April
	1994): 119-31.
<P>
Demmers, Linda, Karen M. G. Howell, and Lucy Siefert Wegner.
	"Envisioning the Library of Tomorrow." <EM>Educators' Tech
	Exchange</EM> 1, no. 3 (Fall 1993): 8-14.
<P>
"Electronic Library Project: ISI & IBM Document Delivery Project."
	<EM>Online Libraries and Microcomputers</EM> 12, no. 8/9 (September
	1994): 5-6.<P>

Garrett, John R. "Digital Libraries: The Grand Challenges." <EM>EDUCOM
	Review</EM> 28, no. 4 (July/August 1993): 17-21.
<P>
Gasaway, Laura N. "Document delivery." <EM>Computers in Libraries</EM> 14, no. 5
	(May 1994): 25-28, 30-32.
<P>
Gasaway, Laura N. "Protecting Intellectual Property." <EM>Bulletin of the
	American Society for Information Science</EM> 19, no. 2
	(December/January 1992-93): 11-15.
<P>
Gasaway, Laura N., and Sarah K. Wiant. <EM>Libraries and Copyright: A Guide
	to Copyright Law in the 1990s</EM>.Washington, DC: Special Libraries Association, 1994.
<P>
Hawkins, Brian L. "Planning for the National Electronic Library."
	<EM>EDUCOM Review</EM> 29, no. 3 (May/June 1994): 19-29.
<P>
Hulser, Richard P. "Overview of Graphical User Interfaces." <EM>Computers
	in Libraries</EM> 13, no. 2 (February 1993): 18-20, 22-23.
<P>
Kotlas, Carolyn M. <EM>Computers and Copyrights: Bibliography</EM>. Durham, NC: Institute for Academic Technology, 1994.
	Available on the Internet at <A HREF="http://www.iat.unc.edu/guides/irg-04.html">http://www.iat.unc.edu/guides/irg-04.html</A> 
<P>
Ladner, Sharyn J., and Hope N. Tillman. <EM>How Special Librarians Really
	Use the Internet: Summary of Findings and Implications for the
	Library of the Future</EM>. Available on the Internet at <A HREF="ftp://hydra.uwo.ca/LibSoft/ SPEC_LIBS.TXT">ftp://hydra.uwo.ca/LibSoft/ SPEC_LIBS.TXT</A>
<P>
Lancaster, F. W., ed. <EM>Libraries and the Future: Essays on the Library
	in the Twenty-First Century</EM>. New York: Haworth Press, 1993.
<P>
Martin, Murray S. The Changing Library Environment." <EM>Library Trends</EM> 42,
	no. 3 (Winter 1994): 478-89.
<P>
McClure, Charles R. and others. "Academic Libraries and the Impact of
	Internet/NREN: Key Issues and Findings." <EM>Proceedings of the
	ASIS Annual Meeting</EM> 30 (1993): 32- 38.
<P>
Neff, Raymond K. "CWRUnet -- Case History of a Campus-Wide
	Fiber-to-the-Desktop Network." <EM>CAUSE/EFFECT</EM> 15, no. 2 (Summer
	1992): 26-29, 33-38.
<P>
OCLC.<EM> The Future is Now: The Changing Face of Technical Services</EM>.
	Proceedings of the OCLC symposium, ALA Midwinter Conference.
	Dublin, OH: OCLC, 1994.
<P>
Reich, Vicky, and Mark Weiser. "Libraries Are More Than Information:
	Situational Aspects of Electronic Libraries." <EM>Serials Review</EM>
	20, no. 3 (Fall 1994): 31-37.
<P>
Risher, Carol A., and Laura N. Gasaway. "The Great Copyright Debate."
	<EM>Library Journal</EM> 119, no. 15 (September 15, 1994): 34-37.
<P>
Shuman, Bruce A. <EM>The Library of the Future</EM>. Englewood, CO: Libraries
	Unlimited, 1989.
<P>
Smith, Eldred. "How to Survive the Present while Preparing for the
	Future: A Research Library Strategy." <EM>College and Research
	Libraries</EM> 54, no. 5 (September 1993): 389-96.
<P>
Stahl, Bil. "Interactive Video Networks: Experiences, Issues and
	Challenges." <EM>Microcomputers for Information Management</EM> 10, no.
	3 (September 1993): 195- 202.
<P>
Stahl, Bil. "Networked Information Resources: Not Just a Library
	Challenge." <EM>CAUSE/EFFECT</EM> 15, no. 3 (Fall 1992): 44-45.
<P>
Stahl, Bil. "Trends and Challenges for Academic Libraries and
	Information Services." <EM>CAUSE/EFFECT</EM> 18, no. 1 (Spring 1995):
	53-55.
<P>
Stevens, Norman. "Anticipatory Reference Service: The Way of the
	Future?" <EM>Reference Librarian</EM> 40 (1993): 3-9.
<P>
Turock, Betty. "Three Business Trends that Strengthen Library
	Operations." <EM>The Bottom Line</EM> 8, no. 1 (Summer 1994): 19-23.
<P>
Tuttle, Marcia. <EM>Introduction to Serials Management</EM>. Greenwich, CT: JAI
	Press, 1983.
<P>
Ulmschneider, John. "Integrated Electronic Document Delivery: Linchpin
	for Campus Information Systems." <EM>EDUCOM Review</EM> 27, no. 6
	(November/December 1992): 42-45.
<P>
Willis, Katherine, and others. "TULIP -- The University Licensing
	Program: Expriences at the University of Michigan." <EM>Serials
	Review</EM> 20, no. 3 (Fall 1994): 39-47.
<P>
