<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>Sources for Reviews of Educational<BR>CD-ROMs and Software</FONT></STRONG>
<P>
Compiled by: Sarah Ivey, IAT Library Assistant<BR>
and Carolyn Kotlas, IAT Librarian<BR>
Institute for Academic Technology<BR>
Last revised: October 27, 1995
</CENTER>
<P>
<STRONG>Education-Oriented Periodicals</STRONG>
<P>
The following periodicals include reviews and evaluations of educational materials on CD-
ROM or educational software packages, either as a regular column or as an occasional 
feature article.
<P>
<EM>Bits & Bytes Review: Reviews & News of Products & Resources for Academic 
Computing</EM>. [ISSN 0891-2955] Whitefish, MT: Bits & Bytes Computer Resources.
<P>
<EM>CAELL Journal: Computer-Assisted English Language Learning Journal</EM>. [ISSN 1049-
9059] Eugene, OR: ISTE (International Society for Technology in Education) 
with the support of CALICO and the TESOL (Teachers of English to Speakers of 
Other Languages) CALL Interest Section.
<P>
<EM>CALICO Journal</EM>. [ISSN 0742-7778] Provo, UT: Computer Aided Language Learning & 
Instruction Consortium (CALICO).
<P>
<EM>CALL: Computer Assisted Language Learning</EM>. [ISSN 0958-8221] Oxford, 
England: Intellect; Lisse, The Netherlands: Swets & Zeitlinger.
<P>
<EM>The Chronicle of Higher Education</EM>. [ISSN 0009-5982] Washington, DC: The Chronicle 
of Higher Education.
	<BR>Available electronically: <A HREF="http://chronicle.merit.edu/.index.html">http://chronicle.merit.edu/.index.html</A>
<P>
<EM>College Mathematics Journal</EM>. [ISSN 0746-8342] Washington, DC: The Mathematical 
Association of America.
<P>
<EM>Collegiate Microcomputer</EM>. [ISSN 0731-4213] Terre Haute, IN: Rose-Hulman Institute of 
Technology.
<P>
<EM>Computational Linguistics</EM>. [ISSN 0891-2017] Cambridge, MA: Association for 
Computational Linguistics.
<P>
<EM>Computers & Education</EM>. [ISSN 0360-1315] New York, NY: Pergamon Press.
<P>
<EM>Computers and the Humanities: Official Journal of The Association for Computers and 
the Humanities</EM>. [ISSN 0010-4817] Dordrecht, The Netherlands; Boston, MA: 
Kluwer Academic Publishers.
<P>
<EM>Computers in Libraries</EM>. [ISSN 1041-7915] Medford, NJ: Information Today, Inc. 
(formerly Learned Information, Inc.)
<P>
<EM>Computing Teacher</EM>. [ISSN 0278-9175] Eugene, OR: International Council for 
Computing in Education.
<P>
<EM>Educational Technology: The Magazine for Managers of Change in Education</EM>. [ISSN 
0013-1962] Englewood Cliffs, NJ: Educational Technology Publications, Inc.
<P>
<EM>Educational Media & Technology Yearbook</EM>. [ISSN 8755-2094] Littleton, CO: Libraries 
Unlimited, Inc.
<P>
<EM>Educators' Tech Exchange</EM>. [ISSN 1065-9447] Pacific Grove, CA: Edutech, Inc.
<P>
<EM>Educom Review</EM>. [ISSN 1045-9146] Washington, DC: Educom, Interuniversity 
Communications Council, Inc.
	<BR>Available electronically: <A HREF="http://www.educom.edu/educom.review/.index.html">http://www.educom.edu/educom.review/.index.html</A>
<P>
<EM>Electronic Learning</EM>. [ISSN 0278-3258] New York, NY: Scholastic, Inc.
<P>
<EM>History Microcomputer Review</EM>. [ISSN 0887-1078] Pittsburg, KS: Dept. of History, Pittsburg State 
University.
<P>
<EM>ICAME Journal: International Computer Archive of Modern English</EM>. [ISSN 0801-5775] 
Bergen, Norway: Norwegian Computing Centre for the Humanities.
<P>
<EM>IDEAL: Issues and Developments in English and Applied Linguistics</EM>. [ISSN 1047-9767] 
Champaign, IL: Division of English as a Second Language, Intensive English 
Institute, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign.
<P>
<EM>Instructor</EM>. [ISSN 1049-5851] New York, NY: Scholastic, Inc.
<P>
<EM>Journal of Computers in Mathematics & Science Teaching</EM>. [ISSN 0731-9258] Austin, 
TX: Association for Computers in Mathematics and Science Teaching.
<P>
<EM>Journal of Computing in Higher Education</EM>. [ISSN 1042-1726] Amherst, MA: Norris 
Publishers.
<P>
<EM>Language Industry Monitor</EM>. [ISSN 0925-3327] Amsterdam, The Netherlands: Uitgverij 
LIM.
<P>
<EM>Language Learning Journal</EM>. [ISSN 0957-1736] Rugby, England: Association for 
Language Learning.
<P>
<EM>Literary & Linguistic Computing</EM>. [ISSN 0268-1145] Oxford, England: Association for 
Literary and Linguistic Computing.
<P>
<EM>Multilingual Computing Magazine</EM>. [ISSN 1065-7657] Clark Fork, ID: Worldwide Pub. 
Group.
<P>
<IMG SRC="../media/gifs/update.gif"> <EM>Multimedia Schools: A Practical Journal of Multimedia, CD-ROM, Online and Internet 
in K-12</EM>. [ISSN 1075-0479] Wilton, CT: Online, Inc.
	<BR>Available electronically: <A HREF="http://www.onlineinc.com/online/online/mmschools/index.html">http://www.onlineinc.com/online/online/mmschools/index.html</A>
<P>
<EM>The Reading Teacher</EM>. [ISSN 0034-0561] Newark, DE: International Reading Association.
<P>
<EM>Research in Humanities Computing</EM>. Oxford: Clarendon Press. (sponsored by The 
Association for Literary and Linguistic Computing and The Association for 
Computers and the Humanities).
<P>
<EM>School Library Journal</EM>. [ISSN 0362-8930] New York, NY: R.R. Bowker Co.
<P>
<EM>School, Science and Mathematics</EM>. [ISSN 0036-6803] Bowling Green, OH: School 
Science and Mathematics Association, Inc.
<P>
<EM>Science Software</EM>. [ISSN 0893-9101] New York, NY: John Wiley & Sons.
<P>
<EM>Social Science Computer Review</EM>. [ISSN 0894-4393] Durham, NC: Duke University 
Press.
<P>
<EM>Syllabus</EM>. [ISSN1065-2086] Sunnyvale, CA: Syllabus Press, Inc.
	<BR>Available electronically: <A HREF="http://www.syllabus.com/">http://www.syllabus.com/</A>
<P>
<EM>Teaching Children Mathematics</EM>. [ISSN 1073-5836] Reston, VA: National Council of 
Teachers of Mathematics.
