<HR>
<CENTER><H2>"Technology Across the Campus: Creating a Student-Centered Environment"</H2>
<P><B>Original Broadcast Date:</B> Thursday, December 2, 1993
<BR>[<A HREF="#overview">Overview</A> | <A HREF="#speakers">Key Speakers</A> | <A HREF="#materials">Supplemental Materials</A> | <A HREF="#video">Video Ordering Information</A>]</CENTER>
<P><HR><P>

<H3><A NAME="overview">Overview</A></H3>

<P>Is your campus looking for ways to focus more on the student? In this video, our panel of experts demonstrates and discusses how information technology can streamline campus services to make your institution more competitive by creating a student-centered environment. You will discover how:

<UL><LI>Students can gain secure electronic access to review their records, order transcripts, track academic progress - 24 hours a day.
<LI>Faculty and staff can focus on the students' individual needs rather than answering routine questions.
<LI>Students can use a new multimedia tool to explore subjects, take charge of their learning and create sophisticated multimedia applications.</UL>

<P>Plus, see how schools across the country have significantly increased their focus on students by using information technology resources, including information kiosks, multimedia learning tools and more.

<H3><A NAME="speakers">Key Speakers</A></H3> 

<UL>
<LI>Darlene Burnett - Consultant in administrative and academic computing, IBM Higher Education.
<LI><A HREF="../../graves/graves.html">William H. Graves</A> - Director of the IAT and Associate Provost for Information Technology, University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.
<LI><A HREF="../../noblitt/noblitt.html">James S. Noblitt</A> - IAT Academic Chair and Research Professor of Romance Languages, University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. 
<LI>Diana G. Oblinger - Academic Programs Manager, IBM Higher Education.
<LI>Douglas D. Short - IAT Fellow and Consultant in multimedia application design and development, IBM Higher Education.
</UL>

<H3><A NAME="materials">Supplemental Materials</A></H3>


<H3><A NAME="video">Video Ordering Information</A></H3>
<UL><LI><A HREF="../vidorder.html">TO ORDER</A>
<LI><A HREF="../resource.html">Information about other videos in the IAT collection</A>
</UL>

