<HR>
<CENTER><H2>"Classroom Design With Technology In Mind"</H2>
<P><B>Original Broadcast Date:</B> Thursday, February 24, 1994
<BR>[<A HREF="#overview">Overview</A> | <A HREF="#speakers">Key Speakers</A> | <A HREF="#materials">Supplemental Materials</A> | <A HREF="#video">Video Ordering Information</A>]</CENTER>
<P><HR><P>

<H3><A NAME="overview">Overview</A></H3>

<P>At an increasing number of educational institutions, technology is finding its way into the classroom and transforming the experience of teaching and learning. In this video we explore the art of creating classrooms that match technological form with pedagogical function. You will discover how to:

<UL><LI>Configure your classroom to address shifts in the teaching/learning paradigm - from lecture-based models to student-based models to collaborative models.
<LI>Incorporate the six basic elements of instructional technology - microcomputers, networks, multimedia, display systems, student response systems and control systems.
<LI>Assign each class to the classroom configuration that best meets its curricular requirements.</UL>

<P>You'll see how different classroom configurations not only facilitate different kinds of classroom interaction, but also create new opportunities for teaching and learning.

<H3><A NAME="speakers">Key Speakers</A></H3> 

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="../../conway/conway1.html">Kathryn Conway</A> - IAT Senior Analyst for Distributed Learning Environments.
<LI>Steven L. Epstein - Consultant in electronic classroom design, IBM Higher Education.
<LI>Steve Griffin - IAT Director of Technical Services.
<LI>David R. Luttrell - IAT Manager of Network Integration Services.
<LI>Jack Wilson - Director of the Anderson Center for Innovation in Undergraduate Education and Professor of Physics, Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute.
</UL>

<H3><A NAME="materials">Supplemental Materials</A></H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="../../../guides/irg-03.html">Computer Classroom and Laboratory Design: Bibliography</A></UL>

<H3><A NAME="video">Video Ordering Information</A></H3>
<UL><LI><A HREF="../vidorder.html">TO ORDER</A>
<LI><A HREF="../resource.html">Information about other videos in the IAT collection</A>
</UL>

