<HR>
<CENTER><H2>"Moving Toward a National Learning Infrastructure"</H2>
<P><B>Original Broadcast Date:</B> Thursday, April 28, 1994
<BR>[<A HREF="#overview">Overview</A> | <A HREF="#speakers">Key Speakers</A> | <A HREF="#materials">Supplemental Materials</A> | <A HREF="#video">Video Ordering Information</A>]</CENTER>
<P><HR><P>

<H3><A NAME="overview">Overview</A></H3>

<P>Campus executives face ever-growing pressures - diminishing resources, increased competition for students, and public demand for accountability and cost containment. In this video, our panel of academic executives and information technology leaders will discuss the concept of a national learning infrastructure and how it will help meet these challenges at a national level. You will discover:

<UL><LI>How national learning efforts relate to the Internet and the national information infrastructure.
<LI>How current technology and sociology affect the development of this infrastructure.
<LI>Why this infrastructure is essential to future academic and public policy development.
<LI>How institutions, organizations and companies can collaborate to implement a learning infrastructure that links the country.</UL>

<P>You'll also see why national strategies to incorporate technology into education will help add value to instruction, increase access to higher education, and address concerns about the cost of education.

<H3><A NAME="speakers">Key Speakers</A></H3> 

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="../../graves/graves.html">William H. Graves</A> - Director of the IAT and Associate Provost of Information Technology, University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.
<LI>Robert C. Heterick - President, Educom.
<LI>Richard L. McCormick - Provost and Vice Chancellor for Academic Affairs and Professor of History, University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.
<LI>Diana G. Oblinger - Academic Programs Manager, IBM Higher Education.
<LI>J. Dennis O'Connor - Chancellor, University of Pittsburgh.
<LI>Carol A. Twigg - Associate Vice Chancellor for Learning Technologies, State University of New York.
</UL>

<H3><A NAME="materials">Supplemental Materials</A></H3>


<H3><A NAME="video">Video Ordering Information</A></H3>
<UL><LI><A HREF="../vidorder.html">TO ORDER</A>
<LI><A HREF="../resource.html">Information about other videos in the IAT collection</A>
</UL>

