<HR>
<CENTER><H2>"Libraries: Today's Issues, Tomorrow's Challenges"</H2>
<P><B>Original Broadcast Date:</B> Thursday, December 1, 1994
<BR>[<A HREF="#overview">Overview</A> | <A HREF="#speakers">Key Speakers</A> | <A HREF="#materials">Supplemental Materials</A> | <A HREF="#video">Video Ordering Information</A>]</CENTER>
<P><HR><P>

<H3><A NAME="overview">Overview</A></H3>

<P>Libraries and information centers have an exciting and challenging role to play in making tomorrow's information technology deliver on its promise. In this video, librarians and library consultants discuss and present guidelines for the following issues confronting the profession:
<UL><LI>Technology in the library.
<LI>Library administration trends.
<LI>Networked information policies.
<LI>New media and copyright.
<LI>Electronic publishing.</UL>

<H3><A NAME="speakers">Key Speakers</A></H3> 

<UL>
<LI>Toni Carbo Bearman - Dean of the School of Library Science at the University of Pittsburgh and a member of the US Advisory Council on the National Information Infrastructure.
<LI>Laura N. Gassaway - Director of the Law Library, University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.
<LI>Carolyn Kotlas - IAT Information Resources Manager.
<LI>Bil Stahl - Director of Information Technology Planning, University of North Carolina at Charlotte.
<LI>Marcia Tuttle - head of the serials department at Davis Library, University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.
<LI>John Ulmschneider - Assistant Director for Library Systems, North Carolina State University Libraries.
</UL>

<H3><A NAME="materials">Supplemental Materials</A></H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="../../../guides/irg-17.html">Libraries: Today's Issues, Tomorrow's Challenges - Bibliography</A> 
</UL>

