<TITLE>Books on Corporate Change</TITLE>
<!-- Created:  August 27, 1996 by Carolyn Kotlas-->
<!-- Last revised: August 30, 1996 -->
<!-- Filename = books.html -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFCE7" TEXT="#00006F" LINK="#006700" VLINK="#8080C0" ALINK="#EE0000">

<FONT SIZE=+1>Books on Corporate Change:</FONT>

<P>

Eccles, Tony. <EM>Succeeding With Change: Implementing Action-Driven Strategies</EM>. Harvard Business School Press, 1996. <BR>ISBN: 0077090047

<A NAME="curve"></A><P>

Imparato, Nicholas, and Oren Harari. <EM>Jumping the Curve: Innovation and Strategic Choice in an Age of Transition</EM>. (Jossey-Bass Management Series.) San Francisco: Jossey-Bass Publishers, 1994. <BR>ISBN: 1555427057

<P>

Janson, Robert, Dennis Attenello, and John Uzzi. <EM>Reengineering for Results: A Step-By-Step Guide</EM>. Quality Resources, 1995. <BR>ISBN: 0527763039

<P>

Luftman, Jerry N., Editor. <EM>Competing in the Information Age: Strategic Alignment in Practice</EM>. Oxford University Press, 1996. <BR>ISBN: 0195090160

<P>

Maurer, Rick. <EM>Beyond the Wall of Resistance: Unconventional Strategies That Build Support for Change</EM>. National Book Network, 1996. <BR>ISBN: 1885167075

<P>

Nevis, Edwin C., Joan Lancourt, and Helen C. Vassallo. <EM>Intentional Revolutions: A Seven-Point Strategy for Transforming Organizations</EM>. (Jossey-Bass Business and Management Series.)  Jossey-Bass Publishers, 1996. <BR>ISBN: 0787902403

<P>

Pasmore, William A. C<EM>reating Strategic Change: Designing the Flexible, High-Performing Organization</EM>. John Wiley & Sons, 1994. <BR>ISBN: 0471597295
