<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP WIDTH="375">


<DL>
<DT><STRONG><FONT  SIZE=+1>IAT Overview</FONT></STRONG>
<DT><A HREF="http://www.unc.edu/">The University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill's</A> <B>Institute for Academic Technology</B> (IAT) is dedicated to the proposition that information technology can be a valuable tool for improving the quality of student learning, increasing access to education, and containing the costs of instruction.  With generous support from <A HREF="http://ike.engr.washington.edu/ike.html">IBM</A>, the IAT facilitates the widespread use of effective and affordable technologies in higher education.  For more information about the Institute and its mission, please read our <A HREF="graves-letter.html">Letter from the Founder</A>.


</DL>
</TD>

<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT  WIDTH="440">
<IMG SRC="../media/gifs/1X17pix.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="17" HEIGHT="300">


Staying informed about changes to the IAT Web</H3>
We update the IAT Web site <B>What's New?</B> section about once a month.  Here are a couple ways to help you easily stay informed of these changes:
<DL>
<DD><IMG SRC="../media/gifs/diabull.gif" WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10 HSPACE="5">Let the <A HREF="http://www.netmind.com/URL-minder/URL-minder.html">URL-Minder</A> inform you, through e-mail, of changes to the IAT Home Page.
<DD><IMG SRC="../media/gifs/diabull.gif" WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10 HSPACE="5">Sign up on the <A HREF="listserv.html">IATNEWS</A> listserv for info on what's happening at the Institute.
</DL>

<P><FONT  SIZE=+1>Questions?</FONT>
For site questions, comments or problems, contact the IAT WebMaster <A HREF="mailto:iatweb@unc.edu">iatweb@unc.edu</A>; 919-560-5031.  

</TABLE>
