<HEAD>
<TITLE>Local Area Network Issues and Strategies</TITLE>
<!-- Created: November 1995 by David Luttrell, IAT-->
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<H1>Local Area Network Issues and Strategies</H1>
<HR><H2>Limitations of Current Networking Topologies and Protocols</H2>
<H3>Ethernet (Coax-Based or Star-Wired UTP) ($100-400 per connection)</H3>
<LI>Approximately 4 1.2Mbps (MPC) Streams
<H3>Token Ring ($300-500 per connection)</H3>
<LI>Approximately 10 1.2Mbps (MPC) Streams
<H3>FDDI ($1500-2000 per connection)</H3>
<LI>Between 40 and 70 1.2Mbps (MPC) Streams
<HR>
<H2>New Networking Standards</H2>
<H3>100MB Ethernet Standards</H3>
<LI>100BaseT (10-30 Connections) ($300-500 per connection )
<LI>100VG-AnyLAN (20-50 Connections)  ($300-500 per connection)

<H3>Switched Ethernet ($400-700 per connection)</H3>
<LI>Approximately 4 1.2Mbps (MPC) Streams <I>Per Segment</I>
<H3>Switched Token Ring ($2000-2400 per connection)</H3>
<LI>Approximately 10 1.2Mbps (MPC) Streams <I>Per Segment</I>
<HR>
<H2>Developing Standards</H2>
<LI>ATM ($4000 per connection)
<LI>1G Ethernet
<LI>Other High Speed Standards (SONET, etc.)
<HR>
<H2>Strategies</H2>
<H3>Category 5 Star Wiring</H3>
Provides for maximum life span of cabling and infrastructure.
<H3>Near Term Transition to Switching</H3>
Provides high performance with simple changes and moderate cost.
<H3>Long Term Transition to ATM</H3>
Provides best Multimedia functionality of any currently planned standard.

<HR><HR>
<H1>Multimedia LAN Technology Resources</H1>
     <DT><A HREF="http://zgdv.igd.fhg.de/papers/multimedia/contents.html" ADD_DATE="815079209" LAST_VISIT="815079180">Information on Multimedia and Hypermedia</A>
      <DT><A HREF="http://www-dse.doc.ic.ac.uk/~np2/multimedia/" ADD_DATE="815077550" LAST_VISIT="815077512">Nat's Distributed Multimedia Index</A>
    <DT><A HREF="http://www.stornet.com/multi.html" ADD_DATE="815078253" LAST_VISIT="815078250">MULTIMEDIA SOLUTIONS</A>
    <DT><A HREF="http://www.theworld.com/COMPUTIN/MULTIMED/SUBJECT.HTM" ADD_DATE="815078610" LAST_VISIT="815078596">TheWorld(TM) Guide to Multimedia</A>
    <DT><A HREF="http://viswiz.gmd.de/MultimediaInfo/" ADD_DATE="815079618" LAST_VISIT="815079615">Index to Multimedia Information Sources</A>
    <DT><A HREF="http://www.amberwave.com/swspots.htm" ADD_DATE="815095550" LAST_VISIT="815095543">Switching Hot Spots</A>
    <DT><A HREF="http://www.alumni.caltech.edu/~dank/fe/" ADD_DATE="815095730" LAST_VISIT="815095670">Dan Kegel's Fast Ethernet Page</A>
</DL>
