<H2>MacWebApp License and Distribution Info</H2>
<I>Copyright 1996 by The University of North Carolina</I><P>
<HR>
<H3>Overview</H3>
<P>This help file contains legally binding information about licensing,
registration and distribution of MacWebApp. If you do not agree
with the conditions and rules stated in this text, please remove
your copy of MacWebApp.

<P>Different terms apply depending on whether you have a SHAREWARE
or REGISTERED copy of MacWebApp. You will know that you have a
SHAREWARE copy if when you run MacWebApp then the first thing
you see is a dialog box stating that it is a SHAREWARE version.

<P>

<H3>Specific Information</H3>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="lic_text.html">Licensing</A> 
<P><LI><A HREF="lic_dist.html">Distribution</A></UL>

<H3>Terms of the Agreement</H3>
<P>In this help topic the following considerations need to be noted:
<UL>
<LI>The term "MacWebApp" identifies release version
of MacWebApp.
<LI>The term "SHAREWARE version" identifies the complete
package containing MacWebApp. By complete package we mean: MacWebApp's
executable file and associated help file.
<LI>The term "SHAREWARE copy" identifies an instance
of the SHAREWARE version.
<LI>The term "REGISTERED version" identifies all other
versions of MacWebApp. The term "REGISTERED copy" identifies
an instance of the REGISTERED version.
</UL>
<P>No component part of MacWebApp may be distributed individually,
disassembled, copied, reverse engineered, or altered in any form.
This includes all elements in the MacWebApp package, interface
items, menus and dialogs, in both REGISTERED and SHAREWARE versions
of the software. 

<BR>
