<PRE>	

</PRE>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>
Institute for Academic Technology Library
</STRONG></FONT></CENTER>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+1><STRONG>Publications</STRONG></FONT>
<P>
The IAT Information Resources staff produces a variety of publications for educators who are interested in incorporating technology into their teaching and research. 
<UL>
<LI><EM><A HREF="../infobits/infobits.html">IAT Infobits</A></EM> -- a monthly electronic newsletter that provides brief summary articles covering information and instruction technology topics in areas of interest to educators
<P>
<LI><A HREF="../guides/guides.html">Information Resource Guides</A> -- bibliographies, source guides, and "webliographies" on education and technology subjects including multimedia technologies, computer classroom design, the Internet, software, and distributed learning
<P>
<LI><EM>IAT Library News</EM> -- in-house newsletter for IAT staff
</UL>
<P><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+1><STRONG>Collections and Services</STRONG></FONT>
<P>
The IAT Information Resources staff maintains a library for the use by all IAT staff and visiting scholars. Our resources include:
<P>
<UL>
<LI> subscriptions to over 350 computer and education technology <A HREF="../cybrary/journals.html">journals, magazines, and
     newsletters </A>
<P>
<LI>nearly 800 books covering educational technology, multimedia development, instructional
     design, and related topics
<P>
<LI>a collection of over 200 CD-ROMs and laserdiscs representing a variety of academic
     disciplines 
<P>
<LI>an extensive collection of <A HREF="../guides/irg-02.html"> vendor catalogs</A> of  educational CD-ROMs, videotapes, laserdiscs, and software
<P>
<LI>a collection of 270 videotapes with viewing equipment available in the Library 
<P>
<LI>a subscription to <EM>Computer Select</EM>, a monthly CD-ROM indexing over 70,000 articles from computer publications, including many articles in full-text
<P>
<LI>a T-1 connection to Internet resources, including online library catalogs, software collections, electronic journals, and electronic text collections 
<P>
<LI>document delivery service through the <A HREF="http://www.carl.org/">CARL UnCover</A> service 
</UL>
<P><BR>
While the IAT Library does not lend materials outside the Institute, visitors may use materials on the premises. To arrange a visit to the IAT Library, send email to <A HREF="mailto:carolyn_kotlas@unc.edu">Carolyn Kotlas</A> or call 919-405-1933.
<P>
