<HR>
<CENTER><H2>Computer Conferencing: Alternative to Lectures
<BR>Selected Bibliography</H2></CENTER>
<P><HR><P>

<P>Barrett, Edward, Ed.  Sociomedia: Multimedia, Hypermedia and the Social Construction of Knowledge.  Cambridge, MA: The MIT Press, 1992.

<P>Bates, Tony.  Technology, Open Learning and Distance Education.  New York: Routledge, 1995.

<P>Berge, Zane L., Ed.  Computer Mediated Communications and the Online Classroom.  Volume I: An Overview and Perspectives.  Cresskill, NJ: Hampton Press, 1995.

<P>Berge, Zane L., Ed.  Computer Mediated Communications and the Online Classroom.  Volume II: Higher Education.  Cresskill, NJ: Hampton Press, 1995.

<P>Berge, Zane L., Ed.  Computer Mediated Communications and the Online Classroom.  Volume III: Distance Learning.  Cresskill, NJ: Hampton Press, 1995.

<P>Burge, Elizabeth J.  Computer Mediated Communication and Education: A Selected Bibliography.  Toronto, Ontario: Ontario Institute for Studies in Education, 1992.

<P>Computer-Mediated Communication for Distance Education: An International Review of Design, Teaching and Institutional Issues.  The American Center for the Study of Distance Education, Monograph No. 6.  University Park, PA: The Pennsylvania State University.

<P>Harasim, Linda, Ed.  Online Education: Perspectives on a New Environment.  New York: Praeger, 1990.

<P>Harasim, Linda, Starr Roxanne Hiltz, Lucio Teles and Murray Turoff.  Learning Networks: A Field Guide to Teaching and Learning Online.  Cambridge, MA: The MIT Press, 1995.

<P>Hiltz, Starr Roxanne.  The Virtual Classroom: Learning Without Limits via Computer Networks.  Human-Computer Interaction Series.  Norwood, NJ: Ablex Publishing Corp., 1994.

<P>Hiltz, Starr Roxanne, and Murray Turoff.  The Network Nation: Communication via Computer.  Cambridge, MA: The MIT Press, 1993.

<P>Mason, Robin, and Anthony Kaye, Eds.  Mindweave: Communication, Computers and Distance Education.  Oxford: Pergamon Press, 1989.

<P>

