                <td valign="top" width="174"><font size="5">T</font>ommy
                Prince conceded he's ''no Stan Brock,'' but
                Monday afternoon, Prince did his best imitation
                of the ''Wild Kingdom'' star as he and others
                chased down a young rhea in the wilds of West
                Knoxville. <p>''It was a circuitous route, maybe
                three (miles), maybe half a mile as the crow
                flies,'' the Knox County school board member
                later joked. </p>
                <p><a href="012197/up_front/up_front.htm"><font
                size="6"><img src="images/icons/menu.gif"
                alt="Menu" align="middle" border="0" width="37"
                height="28"></font></a> </p>
                </td>
                <td width="5">&nbsp;</td>
                <td valign="top" width="250"><p align="left"><img
                src="012197/images/mlk-mp.jpg" width="250"
                height="172"><br>
                <img src="images/v3/credits/MPcredit.gif"
                width="144" height="21"></p>
                <p align="left"><font size="2"><strong>The
                University of Tennessee Black Cultural Committee
                sponsored a march in honor of </strong></font><a
                href="012197/east_ten/4376.htm"><font size="2"><strong>Martin
                Luther King Jr.</strong></font></a><font size="2"><strong>
                from Circle Park to the Student Center on the
                campus Monday afternoon.</strong></font><br>
                </p>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        </center></div></td>
