        <td valign="top" width="430"><p>&nbsp;</p>
       <BASEFONT SIZE="6"><FONT SIZE="6"><B>Orlando magic: Vol fans can sample Citrus smorgasbord</B></FONT><BR><!--SUBHEAD--><P>
</basefont><FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
<FONT SIZE="3"><!--dateline--></FONT></B><BR>
<P>   Florida Citrus Bowl hoopla will shift into high gear on Wednesday, Jan. 1, in Orlando. The New Year&#39;s Day football game between the University of Tennessee and Northwestern University is set for 1 p.m.
<P>   Five days of pre-game activities bring out fans in big numbers. The team is staying at the Renaissance Orlando Resort. President and Mrs. Joe Johnson will be there too.
<P>   The midweek game date presents travel problems for some. People are flying in and flying out in order to get children back for school&#39;s opening on Jan. 2.
<P>    That&#39;s the plan for Mike Moneymaker of Farragut.  He&#39;s taking his daughter, Brandi, 13, and her friend, Haley McCabe, 13.
<P>   &#39;&#39;I don&#39;t think I&#39;ve missed a bowl game since the 1967-68 season,&#39;&#39; says Moneymaker.  He and his wife, Vickie, are UT graduates and big fans.  About 40 friends from Tennessee, Texas and Georgia meet Moneymaker at the bowl games every year.  
<P>   &#39;&#39;I&#39;d rather be there in person than watch it on TV.  I get more out of the game,&#39;&#39; Moneymaker says. He counts this as his seventh trip to Orlando. The family usually takes in all the tourist sites. This year they hope to get to Busch Gardens in Tampa.
<P>Disney fun facts
<P>   If you think University of Tennessee fans are decked out in Big Orange for the Citrus Bowl, then think again when you stroll through Walt Disney World Resort.  The Disney folks really know how to get dressed up!
<P>   It takes about 130 tractor-trailer truckloads to transport all the holiday decorations from the Christmas warehouse to locations throughout Walt Disney World.
<P>   More than 80,000 red, white and pink poinsettias fill flower beds throughout Disney World. 
<P>   Eighteen thousand apples are hung throughout Fort Wilderness Resort and Campground to adorn the resort&#39;s country-themed holiday celebration.
<P>   Four hundred Christmas trees are decorated throughout the Vacation Kingdom.
<P>   More than 14 miles of garland are strung throughout the resort.
<P>Fla. inn directory available
<P>   Visitors to Florida may want to stay at bed and breakfast inns, Southern mansions or small oceanfront resorts. To help them find a place to fit their needs, the Florida Association of Small and Historic Lodging Properties has published a directory.  
<P>   The guidebook describes the inns&#39; unique qualities and maps out locations. It lists 110 properties across the state. To request a copy of &#39;&#39;Inns of Florida,&#39;&#39; call 800 524-1880.
<P>Beaches beckon football fans
<P>   Florida&#39;s Space Coast, just 35 miles east of Orlando, is a perfect destination for vacationers with beach dreams.  
<P>   It is the home of NASA Kennedy Space Center, world-renowned Ron Jon Surf Shop and the largest sea turtle nesting area in the country. Here surfers tame water tunnels, history buffs visit famous sites, art lovers browse through galleries and aviation enthusiasts watch the skies. 
<P>   This 72-mile stretch of Atlantic shore offers affordable family accommodations. To reach Florida&#39;s Space Coast Office of Tourism, call 800 USA-1969.
<P>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        </td>
    </tr>
