<head>
	<title>U.S. seeks to define old-growth forests</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper, Detours, Entertianment, Music, Arts">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><a href="/"><IMG SRC="../../images/flag.gif" ALT="A Knoxville News-Sentinel Online product" border=0></a></center><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 21, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
            <basefont size=6>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>U.S. seeks to define old-growth forests</B></font><!--SUBHEAD--><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I>By Morgan Simmons, News-Sentinel staff writer</I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		</basefont><FONT SIZE="+2">B</FONT>efore making management decisions affecting old-growth forests in the South, the U.S. Forest Service wants answers to a few basic questions.
<P>    Like what is old growth and what isn&#39;t.
<P>    &#39;&#39;Our agency decided to go out to the researchers and scientists and ask them for a definition,&#39;&#39; said Sam Brocato, timber, wildlife and fisheries staff officer for the Cherokee National Forest. &#39;&#39;Once we adopt a set of old-growth criterion, then we can go to the field and inventory what we have.&#39;&#39;
<P>    The findings of the old-growth team are contained in a report titled &#39;&#39;Guidance for Conserving and Restoring Old Growth Forest Communities on the National Forests in the Southern Region.&#39;&#39; The report was published recently as a final draft and is out for public review.
<P>    The document -- a year in the making -- provides old-growth definitions for 16 vegetation types and also establishes procedures for identifying existing and future stands of old growth through field inventories.
<P>    A team of 10 professionals with backgrounds in forest ecology, silviculture, natural resources planning and public affairs contributed to the 100-page report, which addresses old growth in the national forests of all 13 Southern states and will be used in the Forest Service&#39;s upcoming forest-plan revisions for the Cherokee National Forest.
<P>    &#39;&#39;Old growth is a local issue as well as a national issue,&#39;&#39; said Brocato. &#39;&#39;Hopefully, this will provide some common ground for the general public and land managers to agree upon in planning for old growth in the Southeast.&#39;&#39;
<P>    According to the report, existing old-growth communities may represent aound 0.6 percent (approximately 676,000 acres) of the total forest acreage (approximately 108,400,000 acres) in the Southeast.
<P>    The report states that national forests should conserve old-growth communities by developing a network of old-growth restoration areas, leading to a &#39;&#39;forest matrix which includes a full array of forest conditions but which is dominated primarily by mid- and late-successional forests.&#39;&#39;
<P>    The report recognizes the need for public participation and coordination between national forests sharing common ecological boundaries and says: &#39;&#39;Due to the current scarcity of old-growth communities, most of the old-growth efforts on Southern national forests will involve identifying areas for old-growth restoration.&#39;&#39;
<P>    The report lists 16 old-growth communities (nine found in the Cherokee). Examples include Northern hardwood forest, Eastern river-front forest, dry-mesic oak forest, and dry and xeric oak forests, woodlands.
<P>    A set of old-growth parameters -- the mean age of the tree, diameter of the trunk and number of trees per acre -- are provided for each forest type. For example, with hardwood sugar maples, old growth is defined as trees between 100 and 136 years old and measuring between 14 and 38 inches in diameter 41/2 feet up the trunk. The stand density for sugar maples calls for a minimum of 153 old-growth trees per acre.
<P>    &#39;&#39;The old-growth attributes for one forest type may be entirely different for another,&#39;&#39; said Brocato. &#39;&#39;Similarly, our definition of old growth in the Southeast is nothing like what&#39;s used out West. Before we can address the issue of old growth, we have to understand which definitions to use. That first step is provided by this report.&#39;&#39;
<P>
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>
<hr size=5>

	<P><center><font size=2>Return to </font><a href="/"><font size=2>Main</font></a><font size=2>. Copyright &#169; 1996 The Knoxville News-Sentinel. For comments, e-mail </font><a href="mailto:webmaster@www.knoxnews.com"><font size=2>webmaster</font></a><font size=2>.</font></center></p>
