<P><B>CROUSE, ELMER GRAHAM - </B>age 84, died Monday morning, January 20, 1997, in the Smyth County Community Hospital. He was born in Smyth County, Virginia, on February 25, 1912, the son of the late William A. and Minnie Fox Crouse. He was retired from Union Carbide Corporation of Oak Ridge, Tenn. and formerly resided in Farragut area of West Knoxville, Tenn. He is survived by: his wife, Evelyn Pedigo Crouse; one son, Bane Crouse Price of Layton, Utah; one daughter, Estelle Bluhm of Knoxville, Tenn.; three brothers, James W. Crouse of Roanoke, Va., Arnold I. Crouse of Roanoke, Va., and Algie G. Crouse of Marion, Va.; five grandchildren; and several great-grandchildren. Funeral service will be held Wednesday, January 22, 1997, at 2 p.m. at Seaver-Brown Chapel, Marion, Va. with Dr. J.N. Howard and Rev. Carol Ferguson officiating. Burial will follow in the Crouse Family Cemetery on Wasum Valley Road, Marion, Va. The family will receive friends at home anytime or at Seaver-Brown Chapel, Tuesday evening, from 7 until 9 p.m. Seaver-Brown Funeral Service, is in charge of the arrangments.
