<P><B>JONES, DAVID PAUL - </B>68, of East Knoxville, died Sunday, January 19, 1997. He was a U.S. Navy Veteran and a long-time Knoxville dry cleaner. Survivors: wife, Thelma; daughter and son-in-law, Tammy and Ronnie Davis of Blaine; son, Donnie Jones; sons and daughters-in-law, Dale and Judy Jones, Danny and Linda Jones, all of Knoxville; eight grandchildren; and four great-grandchildren; brothers and sisters-in-law, Ralph and Zella Anderson, Earl and Judy Anderson; sister, Mary Thomas; sisters and brothers-in-law, Helen and Bob Ganlding, Martha and Leslie Grant; stepchildren, Janice Henderlight and Cindy Lowery, Allen Bruner, Wayne Lowery and wife, Brenda, Jeff Lowery and wife, Lisa; nine stepgrandchildren; and 11 step-great-grandchildren. Funeral service 2 p.m. Tuesday in Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel. Interment will follow at Highland Memorial Cemetery. Arrangements by Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel, in charge.
