<P><B>SWAGGERTY, INEZ W. - </B>87, 1637 Newbern Road, Kingsport, died Sunday evening, January 19, 1997, at Holston Valley Hospital after a lengthy illness. She was a resident of Brookhaven Health Care Center. She was born in Sevier County, Tenn., and was a resident of Knoxville, Tenn. most of her life. She had made her home in Kingsport since the death of her husband, former Knoxville police officer, Thomas R. Swaggerty. She was preceded in death, in addition to her husband, by her parents, Asa and Addie Watson; four sisters, Abbie McMahan, Emma Watson, Leona Atchley, and Ida Lindsay; two brothers, Homer Watson and Jess Watson; one nephew and one niece. Surviving are: one daughter and son-in-law, Sue and Gordon Hobbs, Kingsport; one grandson, Jeffrey Hobbs, Knoxville, Tenn.; one granddaughter, Vicki Douglas, Kingsport; one great-grandson, Aaron Douglas, Kingsport; one niece, Joann Troutman, Knoxville, Tenn.; two nephews, John Atchley, Jackson, Miss. and Robert Watson, Albany, Ga. Graveside services and burial will be Tuesday, January 21, at 3 p.m. in Greenwood Cemetery, Knoxville, Tenn. Eulogy will be given by Don Troutman. Hamlett-Dobson Funeral Homes, Kingsport in charge of arrangements.
