	<title>Fisher joins First Tennessee as manager of new department</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper Business News">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<a href="/"><img src="../../images/flag.gif" alt="Knoxville News-Sentinel Online -- Business News" align=bottom border=0 width=595 height=176></a><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td align=left valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 21, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>Fisher joins First Tennessee as manager of new department</B></font><basefont size=6><!--SUBHEAD--></basefont></FONT><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		<FONT SIZE="+2">J</FONT>ohn Fisher, formerly city executive and senior vice president of NationsBank in Knoxville, is joining First Tennessee Bank as senior vice president and manager of a newly created Regional Banking Department effective Wednesday.
<P>   The Regional Banking Department will concentrate on lending to financial institutions and middle market companies with sales of more than $10 million within a 250-mile radius of Knoxville. 
<P>   &#39;&#39;In the six years that John has been in Knoxville, he has established an excellent reputation for his leadership in both the financial and local business communities,&#39;&#39; said Larry Martin, chief executive officer of First Tennessee in Knoxville.
<P>   Fisher called First Tennessee &#39;&#39;a progressive organization that shares my beliefs in teamwork and giving to the community.&#39;&#39; 
<P>   Before joining NationsBank, Fisher was regional commercial bank coordinator for First Union Bank in Fort Lauderdale, Fla.
<P>   Fisher is president and director of the Knoxville Opera Company, chairman of the endowment committee for the Boys and Girls Club, a trustee of Pellissippi State Technical Community College, a University of Tennessee chancellor&#39;s associate, a pacesetter chairman for the Great Smoky Mountains Boy Scout Council.
<P>   Fisher sits of the boards of the University of Tennessee Theatre, the Greater Knoxville Chamber of Commerce and The Downtown Organization.
<P>
