<html>

<head>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type"
content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
<title>Knoxville News-Sentinel ADD Services</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<p><img src="coloraddlogo.gif" alt="Additional Direct Delivery"
width="350" height="109">&nbsp;</p>

<p>Additional Direct Delivery (ADD) is a wholly owned subsidiary
of the Knoxville News Sentinel Company. We are affiliated with
Alternate Postal Delivery, Inc. (ADD) of Grand Rapids, Michigan.</p>

<p>Operating nationally, ADD provides large mailers of second and
third class mail with a cost-efficient delivery alternative to
the United States Postal Service.</p>

<p>Additionally, this service allows local and national
advertisers to distribute demographically targeted flyers, brochures,
samples, etc. more economically than direct mail.</p>

<h4 align="center"><u>ADD's MARKET FACTS</u></h4>

<p><strong>Established in 1991.</strong></p>

<p><strong>Serves Knoxville (Knox Co.), Oak Ridge &amp; Clinton
(Anderson Co.), Seymour (Sevier Co.), Maryville &amp; Alcoa
(Blount Co.).</strong></p>

<p><strong>Homes Delivered Weekly 155,000.</strong></p>

<p><strong>Delivery Method is limited to Door Knob, Newspaper
Tube, and Mail Post Hooks in rural areas.</strong></p>

<p><strong>Services Offered:</strong></p>

<ul>
    <li>Zip Code and Carrier Route Saturation.</li>
    <li>Address Specific</li>
    <li>Magazine Ride-A-Longs.</li>
    <li>Sample Delivery.</li>
    <li>Customized Bags.</li>
    <li>Demographic Profiling.</li>
    <li>Combo Direct Delivery with U.S.P.S. Labeling.</li>
    <li>Address List Maintenance.</li>
    <li>C.A.S.S. Certified Labeling.</li>
</ul>

<h4 align="center"><strong><u>ADD's DIRECT DISTRIBUTION PROGRAM</u></strong></h4>

<p>This Quality Award winning facility delivers our customers
products weekly using a dedicated adult carrier force of
independent contractors. Delivery begins on Tuesday and ends by 7
pm of Wednesday of each week. Optional delivery windows are
available with some price modification.</p>

<p>Verification is maximized with a team of Independent Quality
Control Representatives. These individuals are in the field
within one hour of delivery commencement and armed with a tape
recorder, polaroid camera, pager, and 15 randomly selected
addresses per route. Their goal is to ensure early detection of
problems and accurate delivery of your product.</p>

<h4 align="center"><strong><u>ADD's NEWCOMERS PACKAGE</u></strong></h4>

<p><img src="addmag.jpg" align="right" hspace="7" vspace="7"
width="144" height="149">The Arrival Survival Kit is an exciting
advertising package delivered to newcomers in Knox County and
select zip codes of Blount, Anderson and Sevier Counties -- households
that need to know about your products and services. A service of Additional Direct
Delivery and The Knoxville News-Sentinel, Arrival Survival is an excellent opportunity
to attract new customers. For less than the cost of direct mail, you can advertise
in the kit with:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Inserts, brochures and catalogs.</li>
    <li>Product samples.</li>
    <li>Advertising specialties (refrigerator magnets, calendars,
        etc.).</li>
    <li>Advertisements on the plastic delivery bag.</li>
</ul>

<h4 align="center"><strong><u>ADD's CLARITAS MAPPING SYSTEM</u></strong></h4>

<p>ADD is equipped with Claritas Mapping System - one of the most advanced desktop market
analysis reporting and mapping systems designed to increase media targeting accuracy. ADD's
Claritas Mapping System helps you pinpoint potential customers in
the Knoxville retail marketplace.</p>

<p>With Claritas, ADD can show you where your customers live
within a trade area, show market penetration by census tract or
zip code, and analyze spending patterns. Claritas can also
illustrate your customers newspaper reading habits and help you
locate new stores.<img src="addmap.gif" align="right" hspace="7"
vspace="7" width="400" height="370">&nbsp; </p>
