<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
<title>Quick facts</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<p align="center"><a href="/"><img src="../../images/flag.gif"
alt="A Knoxville News-Sentinel Online product" border="0"
width="595" height="176"></a><br clear="all">
</p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="10">
    <tr>
        <td valign="top" width="150"><i>December 29, 1996</i> </td>
        <td width="470"><font size="6"><b>Quick facts<!--SUBHEAD--></b></font><p><br>
        </p>
        <p>The government defines disability as ''the inability
        to engage in any substantial gainful activity by reason
        of any medically determinable physical or mental
        impairment which can be expected to result in death or
        has lasted or can be expected to last for a continuous
        period of not less than 12 months.'' </p>
        <p>Two kinds of disability payments: </p>
        <p><b>Social Security Disability Insurance, or SSDI</b>:
        This payment is for adults who have worked in the past
        but became disabled. </p>
        <p><b>Supplemental Security Income, or SSI</b>: This
        payment is essentially a welfare check, given to disabled
        individuals with little or no work history or income. </p>
        <p><b>Disability payments </b></p>
        <p><b>United States </b></p>
        <p><b>Total: </b>10.8 million disability checks worth
        about $5.1 billion are mailed monthly. </p>
        <p><b>SSI:</b> 4,984,467 disabled recipients got
        $1,941,278,000 monthly </p>
        <p><b>SSDI:</b> 5,858,000 disabled workers and family
        members got $3,155,000,000 monthly </p>
        <p>Average monthly SSDI benefit for a disabled worker:
        $682 </p>
        <p>Average monthly SSI disability benefit: $389 </p>
        <p><b>Tennessee </b></p>
        <p><b>Total: </b>More than 300,000 checks worth about
        $136 million are sent to Tennesseans monthly </p>
        <p><b>SSI:</b> 145,119 disabled adults and children got
        $51,210,000 million monthly </p>
        <p><b>SSDI:</b> 166,811 disabled workers, spouses and
        children got $84,657,000 per month </p>
        <p>Some individuals receive both SSI and SSDI. </p>
        <p><font size="2"><strong>Source: Social Security
        Administration, December 1995 </strong></font></p>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>

<hr size="5">

