<h1>The Frank Munger Collection</h1>

<p><img src="../images/mugs/munger.gif" align="left" hspace="7"
vspace="7" width="75" height="111">Staff writer Frank Munger
covers Oak Ridge National Laboratory for <i>The Knoxville
News-Sentinel</i>. In addition to his regular news stories,
Munger writes a weekly feature on scientists at work, and an
opinion piece on the goings-on in Oak Ridge. </p>

<p><br clear="all">
</p>

<ul>
    <li>Monday's <a href="/features/munlab.html"><b>In the Lab</b></a>
    </li>
    <li>Wednesday's <a href="/features/munedit.html"><b>Opinion
        Column</b></a> </li>
</ul>

<p><br clear="all">
</p>

<p>Frank Munger covers the Department of Energy's Oak Ridge
operations. He is doing a series of weekly reports on the Y-12
nuclear weapons plant focusing on people and issues in the
post-Cold War era. These special reports appear in Munger's
column on the editorial page. An <a
href="features/munedit/fm081196.html">introduction</a> appeared
Aug 11, 1996 in the Perspective Section. It had his perspective
from researching the plant.. </p>

<p><a href="/register.html"><img src="/images/icons/reg3.gif"
alt="Register" align="left" border="0" hspace="5" vspace="5"
width="63" height="55"></a><a
href="http://ww3.knoxnews.com/register.html"><font size="4">REGISTER</font></a><font
size="4"> for a chance to win a free book about the University of
Tennessee</font> <br clear="all">
</p>

