<title>Knoxville News-Sentinel -- Bookmark Us!</title>
<base href="http://www.knoxnews.com/">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<p align="center"><img src="/images/flag.gif"
alt="The Knoxville News-Sentinel Online" width="578" height="167"><br>
</p>

<h1>Add Us As A Bookmark</h1>

<p>All Web browsers we know of give you the option to add a site
to a list of bookmarks or favorite places you want to re-visit.
We hope you'll put The Knoxville News-Sentinel Online on your
list. Bookmark our homepage, whose Uniform resource Locator, or
URL, is <a href="http://www.knoxnews.com/">http://www.knoxnews.com/</a>.
If you haven't already bookmark us by following this link and
doing one of the things below. </p>

<p><b>Netscape Navigator</b> calls these <em>bookmarks</em>. To
add The Knoxville News-Sentinel Online as a bookmark, go under
the top menu item <strong>Bookmarks</strong>, then select the
option to <strong>Add Bookmark</strong>. No sweat. It will set a
bookmark to whatever document you are viewing when the <strong>Add
Bookmark</strong> command is made. Do it while you're on our main
page. </p>

<p>To use the bookmark, select the bookmark directly from the <strong>Bookmarks</strong>
menu.<br>
</p>

<p><b>Microsoft Internet Explorer</b> calls them <em>Favorites</em>.
Click on <strong>Favorites</strong> then click on <strong>Add to
Favorites</strong>. Like Netscape, you need to have the page you
want to add to your list of favorite sites on the screen when you
add it. Nothing to it. </p>

<p><b>Lynx</b> calls them <em>bookmarks</em>. To add The
Knoxville News-Sentinel as a bookmark, type <kbd>'a'</kbd> (for <strong>add
bookmark</strong>) and then type <kbd>'d'</kbd> (saving the <strong>document</strong>
to a bookmark file). It's that simple. Remember, it will set a
bookmark to whatever document you are viewing when you save the
bookmark. </p>

<p>To use the bookmark, simply type <kbd>'v'</kbd> (for <strong>view
bookmarks</strong>) and, using the up/down arrow or tab keys if
necessary, move to Knoxville News-Sentinel Online and hit return
or enter.</p>

<p align="center">&nbsp;</p>

<hr size="5">

