<table border="0" cellpadding="6" width="600">
    <tr>
        <td align="right" width="360"><img src="jh/clay.gif"
        alt="At the Zoo" align="top" width="355" height="240"
        naturalsizeflag="0"></td>
        <td valign="top"><br>
        <font size="2" face="Arial,Helvetica,Frutiger">A goat at
        the Children's zoo eyes a piece of grass held by Daniel
        Bertram, 21-months-old, at The Knoxville Zoo. &quot;I was
        enterprising for standalone art, and stopped by the zoo.
        After looking around for a while I noticed this little
        girl eyeing the goat. The goat was eyeing her back. The
        picture came together in front of me, and by framing the
        situation with the sign I felt like I had a shot at a
        humerous moment in everyday life,&quot; said Owen.
        Bertram was visiting the zoo in October with her
        grandparents, Walter and Maudean Davis of Clarkrange,
        Tenn. 1996. <b><i>Photo by Clay Owen</i></b></font></td>
    </tr>
</table>
