        gives the thumbs-up sign to supporters as he leaves
        McGhee Tyson Airport when he visited Knoxville in October
        during his successful re-election campaign. &quot;It is
        unusual to see the President and Vice President together
        outside of Washington, DC. said Patrick who felt like he
        caught a special moment. 1996. <br>
        <b><i>Photo by Michael Patrick.</i></b><b> </b></font></p>
