<HEAD>
<TITLE>The AccuWeather U.S. Summary</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">




<center>

<img src="static/accureg.gif" width=150 height=24><br>
<img src="static/natsumhd.gif" width=300 height=24>

<p>
<img src="static/twodot.gif" width=480 height=3 border=0>
<p>

<table border=0
           align=center
           cellpadding=0
           cellspacing=0
           colspec="l75 c5 c20"
           units=relative
           width=100%>

<tr>
<td width=400
       colspan=1
       valign=top>

A storm (29.85) was east of Maine with a cold front extending
southwestward into northeastern New Jersey. A storm (29.39) was over
northwestern North Dakota with a cold front extending to a storm
(29.63) over northern Nebraska where the front continued through
southwestern New Mexico A warm front extended southward from the storm
in Kansas into southern Oklahoma. Another warm front extended
southeastward from the storm in North Dakota into southwestern Ohio. A
storm (29.56) was along the southwestern British Columbia coast with a
cold front extending southward through western Washington and Oregon
then southwestward through central California out into the Pacific
Ocean. High pressure centers were over the Florida Panhandle (30.30)
and southeastern Ontario (30.32).


<td width=10>&nbsp;

<td width=190
      align=center
      bgcolor=#ffffd1
      colspan=1
      valign=top>

