<HEAD>
<TITLE>AccuWeather's Weather Almanac</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">




<center>

<img src="static/accureg.gif" width=150 height=24><br>
<img src="static/wxalmhd.gif" width=279 height=25>

<p>
<img src="static/twodot.gif" width=480 height=3 border=0>
<p>

<table border=0
           align=center
           cellpadding=0
           cellspacing=0
           colspec="l75 c5 c20"
           units=relative
           width=100%>

<tr>
<td width=400
       colspan=1
       valign=top>

<h2>
<pre>
January 21, 1997
</pre>
</h2>
</blockquote>



<table border=1 cellpadding=3>

<TR>
<TH width=100>LOCATION</TH>
<TH>YEAR</TH>
<TH width=330>EVENT</TH>
</TR>


<TR>
<TH width=100 align=left>Sacramento, CA</TH>
<TD align=center>1854</TD>
<TD width=330>
<pre><font size=-2>Coldest day of famous cold California
winter: 19 degrees at Sacramento.
</font></pre>
</TR>

<TR>
<TH width=100 align=left>Fredericksburg</TH>
<TD align=center>1863</TD>
<TD width=330>
<pre><font size=-2>Infamous "Mud March" at Fredericksburg
foiled Union offensive plans.
</font></pre>
</TR>

<TR>
<TH width=100 align=left>Northwest U.S.</TH>
<TD align=center>1921</TD>
<TD width=330>
<pre><font size=-2>"The Great Olympic Blowdown" -- Northead,
WA, had a wind speed of 113 mph with gusts
to 150 mph. Pressure 978.7 mb 128.90".
</font></pre>
</TR>

<TR>
<TH width=100 align=left>Danner, OR</TH>
<TD align=center>1930</TD>
<TD width=330>
<pre><font size=-2>Minus 52 degrees -- minimum for Oregon.
</font></pre>
</TR>

<TR>
<TH width=100 align=left>Winthrop, WA</TH>
<TD align=center>1935</TD>
<TD width=330>
<pre><font size=-2>52 inches of snow -- 24-hour state record.
</font></pre>
</TR>

<TR>
<TH width=100 align=left>Southwest U.S.</TH>
<TD align=center>1983</TD>
<TD width=330>
<pre><font size=-2>Snowstorm; some amounts:

Amarillo, TX 	  9.0 inches
Lubbock, TX 		 17.0 inches
Tucumcari, NM 	  7.5 inches
Clovis, NM 		 11.0 inches

</font></pre>
</TR>

<TR>
<TH width=100 align=left>North Carolina</TH>
<TD align=center>1985</TD>
<TD width=330>
<pre><font size=-2>Minus 34 degrees at Mt. Mitchell --
all-time state record low.
</font></pre>
</TR>

<TR>
<TH width=100 align=left>Johnstown, PA</TH>
<TD align=center>1990</TD>
<TD width=330>
<pre><font size=-2>High winds with a peak gust of 61 mph.
</font></pre>
</TR>
