<h1>Sign Our Guest Book And You Might 
Win A Free Book!</h1>
<p>We know these guest books are a pain so we decided to make it a little fun. Each week (YES, 
week!), we'll be giving away a copy of <i>Tennessee / A Celebration of 150 Years of the 
University</i>.</p>
<p>This 128 page glossy book was published in 1994 by Scripps Howard Publishing. The text was 
written by Betsy B. Creekmore and the introduction was written by News-Sentinel columnist Sam 
Venable.</p>
<p>It contains lots of wonderful UT related photos. Heck, seeing what media meteor Chris Whittle 
(remember him?) looked like in 1967 is worth registering to get a shot at winning a book. We'll 
randomly choose the winner each Monday and post their name here. Of course, no purchase is 
necessary to enter. We've made the form as short as possible so you need to fill out all the blanks 
so we can get the book to you if you win. </p>
<p>This week's (1/13/97) winner is <font size=4>Glann Leen</font> of Max Meadows, VA. Way to go Glann! </p>
