<head>
	<title><!--Use the Headline for HTML Page Title--> How much exercise and of what kind is enough?</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<center><a href="/"><IMG SRC="../../images/flag.gif" ALT="A Knoxville News-Sentinel Online product" border=0></a></center><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top width=150>
		<i><!--Connections 32 with WebDesk Inserts Date Here-->January 15, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B><!--Connections 32 with WebDesk Inserts Headline Here--> How much exercise and of what kind is enough?</B></font><!--Connections 32 with WebDesk Inserts Subheadline Here--><basefont size="6"<!--SUBHEAD--></basefont><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I><!--Connections 32 with WebDesk Inserts Byline Here--></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I><!--Connections 32 with WebDesk Inserts Dateline Here--></I></FONT><BR>
		<!--Connections 32 with WebDesk Inserts Story Text Here--><P>   <B>A.</B> The recently released Surgeon General&#39;s report on physical activity and health made it clear a sedentary lifestyle is damaging the health of Americans and is a major factor for the growing obesity problem in this country.
<P>   What&#39;s being recommended is you don&#39;t have to do all your exercising at one time. Everyone can substantially improve their health and quality of life by accumulating 30 minutes or more of physical activity daily.
<P>   Instead of taking a traditional exercise break, park your car further away from the door, and walk (no strolling) around the building before entering. During the day take your breaks to walk up and down the stairs.
<P>   If you can set aside 30 minutes daily for a brisk walk, you can burn at least 100 calories -- which once a day is 3,000 calories a month, which is almost one pound. 
<P>   Over a year that&#39;s more than 10 pounds.
<P>   
<P>
<P><font size=2>
<P><B>Information prepared by Joy Powell, registered dietitian. Have a question for a dietitian? Send it to Ask-A-Dietitian, Knoxville District Dietetic Association, P.O. Box 50142, Knoxville, TN 37950-0142 or call</B> <B>Dial-A-Dietitian, 524-4541./font>
<P></B>
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>
